WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:32.509 --> 01:36.804
<i>Thirty-two teams, seven rounds,</i>

01:36.805 --> 01:40.605
<i>224 young men who, today,</i>

01:40.684 --> 01:45.405
<i>are about to become players in
the National Football League.</i>

01:45.856 --> 01:48.529
<i>A day where lives are changed,</i>

01:49.109 --> 01:51.657
<i>fates are decided,</i>

01:51.903 --> 01:54.655
<i>dynasties are born,</i>

01:54.656 --> 01:58.285
<i>and the clock is always ticking.</i>

01:58.577 --> 02:00.670
<i>Of course,</i>

02:00.912 --> 02:02.747
<i>I'm talking about...</i>

02:33.070 --> 02:34.571
Hello.

02:36.281 --> 02:37.782
Yes, sir.

02:39.117 --> 02:40.618
Sir?

02:41.620 --> 02:42.703
What is it?

02:42.704 --> 02:44.877
He's waiting in his office.

02:44.998 --> 02:46.290
What time is it?

02:46.291 --> 02:47.792
4:15.

02:52.798 --> 02:54.173
What are we gonna do with it?

02:54.174 --> 02:57.385
Well, we've gone over
this a lot, Walt.

02:57.386 --> 02:59.720
I'm really nervous about
trading away the top pick.

02:59.721 --> 03:00.846
Callahan could be huge.

03:00.847 --> 03:02.098
That's true.

03:02.099 --> 03:04.100
But it might be worth it if
someone's willing to give us

03:04.101 --> 03:06.644
their weight in gold to get him.

03:06.645 --> 03:07.770
What'd the Rams get

03:07.771 --> 03:09.480
when they traded away
number two overall

03:09.481 --> 03:11.148
to the Redskins a few years back?

03:11.149 --> 03:13.984
Three number one picks
and a number two.

03:13.985 --> 03:15.820
Well, shit, that'd work for me.

03:15.821 --> 03:18.072
Nobody's offering us that, Walt.

03:18.073 --> 03:19.620
Look.

03:20.242 --> 03:23.119
Do you want the entire city of
Seattle calling for our heads

03:23.120 --> 03:26.214
because we didn't pick Bo Callahan?

03:27.541 --> 03:30.626
Our fans know a good deal
when they see one, Tom.

03:30.627 --> 03:33.212
Which is why we're not even
gonna think about doing this

03:33.213 --> 03:34.755
unless we can find someone...

03:34.756 --> 03:36.716
Stupid enough to give
us more than he should.

03:36.717 --> 03:37.800
Exactly.

03:37.801 --> 03:39.427
So,

03:40.679 --> 03:43.853
who's the most desperate
guy you know?

03:52.941 --> 03:54.567
<i>We got a fun one today,
don't we, fellas?</i>

03:54.568 --> 03:55.818
<i>Boom, more intrigue this year</i>

03:55.819 --> 03:57.153
<i>than I can remember in a long time.</i>

03:57.154 --> 03:59.155
<i>There's no intrigue at
the number one pick.</i>

04:00.449 --> 04:02.950
<i>Bo Callahan, Wisconsin Badger,
overall number one to Seattle.</i>

04:02.951 --> 04:04.034
<i>That's gotta be a slam dunk.</i>

04:04.035 --> 04:05.327
<i>We haven't had a
quarterback like this</i>

04:05.328 --> 04:07.079
<i>enter the Draft since Andrew Luck.</i>

04:07.080 --> 04:08.456
<i>Right, so you got the
Heisman Trophy winner</i>

04:08.457 --> 04:10.040
<i>going to the Seahawks.</i>

04:10.041 --> 04:12.793
<i>But what about the other 31 teams?
What are they gonna do?</i>

04:12.794 --> 04:14.378
<i>Who you lookin' at today, Jon? Mel?</i>

04:14.379 --> 04:16.505
<i>I think it's Cleveland
at number seven.</i>

04:16.505 --> 04:18.716
<i>Sonny Weaver Jr., he's gotta have
a lot on his mind this year.</i>

04:18.716 --> 04:19.800
<i>I'm with Mel.</i>

04:19.801 --> 04:23.512
<i>As we all know, Sonny's dad, former
Browns coach Sonny Weaver Sr.,</i>

04:23.513 --> 04:26.098
<i>he's a legend in Cleveland,
he died last week.</i>

04:26.099 --> 04:29.810
<i>This kid, Ray Jennings, Heisman
Trophy finalist his senior year.</i>

04:29.811 --> 04:33.355
<i>2,159 combined yards,
running the ball,</i>

04:33.356 --> 04:35.441
<i>catching the ball, 22 touchdowns.</i>

04:35.442 --> 04:37.109
<i>He's looking to take
it to the house.</i>

04:37.110 --> 04:40.029
<i>The only downfall is this guy
got into a little skirmish.</i>

04:40.030 --> 04:43.032
<i>Assault and battery, landed
a kid in the hospital.</i>

04:43.033 --> 04:46.494
<i>But guess what? He was a
model citizen up until then.</i>

04:46.495 --> 04:48.704
<i>And you guys know me.
I'm all about values.</i>

04:48.705 --> 04:50.706
<i>And this kid's number
two on my board.</i>

04:50.707 --> 04:52.958
<i>And when I look at that
incident, I kind of say, "Look.</i>

04:52.959 --> 04:54.251
<i>"It's not medical,
it's not drug-related."</i>

04:54.252 --> 04:55.920
Good morning.

04:55.921 --> 04:57.963
<i>So if I got a kid at number two,</i>

04:57.964 --> 05:00.382
<i>and he's slidin' down
towards number seven...</i>

05:09.976 --> 05:11.853
You look nice.

05:13.396 --> 05:15.689
Are you gonna say anything to me?

05:15.690 --> 05:17.942
Anything at all?

05:19.236 --> 05:20.694
Well, it's big.

05:20.695 --> 05:23.038
It's a pretty big thing
we're talkin' about here.

05:27.953 --> 05:29.620
Look.

05:29.621 --> 05:33.249
You can understand why
this week, of all weeks,

05:33.250 --> 05:35.251
I might feel just a
little conflicted about

05:35.252 --> 05:37.378
the news I'm suddenly
gonna be a dad.

05:37.379 --> 05:38.796
I know.

05:38.797 --> 05:40.765
Shit timing.

05:56.940 --> 05:58.023
Hey!

05:59.109 --> 06:00.906
Hey!

06:05.740 --> 06:07.867
Where are you goin'?

06:07.951 --> 06:09.827
I need to go to my
place before work.

06:11.204 --> 06:12.788
Look, I'm, uh...

06:21.006 --> 06:22.507
Shit.

06:27.304 --> 06:29.513
Hey, Tom. You're up early.

06:29.514 --> 06:31.307
<i>Well, it is Draft Day.</i>

06:31.308 --> 06:32.892
<i>How're you doin'?</i>

06:32.893 --> 06:34.393
Uh... Well, I'm great.
I'm havin' a great day.

06:34.394 --> 06:35.644
How 'bout you?

06:35.645 --> 06:38.398
Well, I'm sittin' here,
eatin' my pancakes,

06:39.274 --> 06:41.233
thinkin' about movin' number one.

06:41.234 --> 06:42.526
Really?

06:42.527 --> 06:47.578
<i>Yeah, as you know, Connors did
a great job for us last year.</i>

06:47.699 --> 06:49.533
But Callahan looks like...

06:49.534 --> 06:50.743
Well, hell, Sonny, he's gonna be

06:50.744 --> 06:53.078
a franchise player for someone.

06:53.079 --> 06:54.956
You'd consider a trade?

06:55.832 --> 06:58.300
I'd consider the right one.

07:02.339 --> 07:05.799
Well, Jesus, Tom, at least act
like you called me, all right?

07:05.800 --> 07:07.259
What do you want for it?

07:07.260 --> 07:10.763
I want your first pick this year,
your first-rounder next year,

07:10.764 --> 07:12.431
and your third-rounder
the year after that.

07:12.432 --> 07:14.975
Ouch. Ouch. No, thanks.

07:14.976 --> 07:16.060
I know what it sounds like...

07:16.061 --> 07:17.895
It sounds like you're trying
to take advantage of me.

07:17.896 --> 07:19.355
I would never do that.

07:19.356 --> 07:21.106
Your seventh pick gives you, what?

07:21.107 --> 07:22.733
A running back with a rap sheet?

07:22.734 --> 07:24.234
You don't know who I'm
pickin' seven, Tom.

07:24.235 --> 07:26.403
I'm not gonna sell the
farm for one guy.

07:26.404 --> 07:27.905
Well...

07:28.365 --> 07:31.209
You should. Your farm sucks.

07:31.409 --> 07:33.077
Pick number one.

07:33.078 --> 07:34.244
Get Bo Callahan.

07:34.245 --> 07:35.329
I got a quarterback.

07:35.330 --> 07:36.831
Brian Drew?

07:37.374 --> 07:39.421
Are you talking about Brian Drew?

07:39.459 --> 07:41.168
Jesus, you're hilarious.

07:41.169 --> 07:42.795
Guy barely made it
through half the season

07:42.796 --> 07:44.713
before gettin' injured last year.

07:44.714 --> 07:46.882
I have the golden ticket, Sonny.

07:46.883 --> 07:51.263
If I give it to you, you get
to save football in Cleveland.

07:54.808 --> 07:58.357
You have 10 seconds, but
then I gotta go to work.

08:01.773 --> 08:04.321
Enjoy your pancakes, Tom.

08:11.491 --> 08:13.492
<i>Folks, I believe the
word "Clevelander"</i>

08:13.493 --> 08:17.705
<i>comes from the Latin word that means
"to have idiotic hope at all time,"</i>

08:17.706 --> 08:20.082
<i>and don't we ever?</i>

08:20.083 --> 08:24.420
<i>We don't have beaches and
beautiful weather and sunshine</i>

08:24.421 --> 08:27.006
<i>and hot babes
roller-skating all over.</i>

08:27.007 --> 08:28.716
<i>You know what we've got?</i>

08:28.717 --> 08:31.385
<i>We got our sports teams.</i>

08:31.386 --> 08:33.011
<i>And that's the only hope we have.</i>

08:33.013 --> 08:34.722
<i>Let me explain to you.</i>

08:34.722 --> 08:38.642
<i>Football was invented 20 miles
down the road in Canton, Ohio.</i>

08:38.643 --> 08:41.602
<i>This is a football town.
It's in our DNA.</i>

08:41.604 --> 08:42.980
<i>No doubt about it.</i>

08:42.981 --> 08:45.649
<i>To me, losing the team altogether,</i>

08:45.650 --> 08:50.696
<i>having the team go and move to
Baltimore, go there and win,</i>

08:50.697 --> 08:52.781
<i>that was so painful for the town.</i>

08:52.782 --> 08:56.832
<i>And then the new expansion
franchise having to come back in.</i>

08:57.245 --> 08:59.288
<i>One of the amazing
things to me is that,</i>

08:59.289 --> 09:03.292
<i>in the midst of all of this losing,
people are still hopeful that...</i>

09:03.293 --> 09:07.379
<i>- Yeah.
- ...eventually, this is going to be our year.</i>

09:07.380 --> 09:11.133
<i>Maybe to a fault, with the hope.
But that's really all we have.</i>

09:11.134 --> 09:14.344
<i>- Because this is a sports town.
- And I want Sonny Weaver to know...</i>

09:14.345 --> 09:16.138
<i>Sonny, I hope you're listening.
You better be.</i>

09:16.139 --> 09:20.601
<i>Can you please do somethin' tonight
to turn this thing around?</i>

09:20.602 --> 09:24.322
<i>- Otherwise, you will be gone.</i>

09:24.814 --> 09:25.898
Hello?

09:25.899 --> 09:28.609
Good morning, Mr. Sonny Weaver Jr.

09:28.610 --> 09:31.612
It's your number one
fan, Vontae Mack.

09:31.613 --> 09:33.447
Vontae, how'd you get this number?

09:33.448 --> 09:36.371
You gave it to me. At the Combine.

09:36.493 --> 09:38.118
It's all right if I called?

09:38.119 --> 09:39.620
That's all right.
It doesn't matter.

09:39.621 --> 09:42.456
Vontae, the Draft doesn't
start until 8:00.

09:42.457 --> 09:44.041
Where are you? New York?

09:44.042 --> 09:45.542
Naw, man.

09:45.543 --> 09:47.920
They wanted me up
there at Radio City,

09:47.921 --> 09:50.594
but I wanted to be here in
Virginia with my grams.

09:50.840 --> 09:53.718
Since she old, she
can't make that trip.

09:54.135 --> 09:55.636
So?

09:55.929 --> 09:57.846
Who you picking?

09:57.847 --> 09:58.972
If I was you,

09:58.973 --> 10:01.141
I'd take a lightning-quick
middle linebacker

10:01.142 --> 10:03.690
who can murder the gaps in a 3-4.

10:03.812 --> 10:05.062
Totally agree.

10:05.063 --> 10:07.648
You got Reggie Wilson's
number down there in Purdue?

10:07.649 --> 10:10.067
Now, I really don't
find that funny.

10:10.068 --> 10:13.445
Yeah, it's funny, Vontae. You're
just not feelin' it right now.

10:13.446 --> 10:16.615
Look, there's gonna be a lot of ups
and downs before this is all over.

10:16.616 --> 10:18.700
Try and keep a sense of humor.

10:18.701 --> 10:20.661
I ain't stupid.

10:20.662 --> 10:24.623
You don't take me at seven,
I'll drop down to the late teens.

10:24.624 --> 10:25.999
I watch the mock drafts!

10:26.000 --> 10:29.211
I know who takin' who and I
can't afford to fall that far.

10:29.212 --> 10:31.630
I can't take no
late-teens paycheck.

10:31.631 --> 10:34.550
Vontae needs a seven-pick paycheck.

10:34.551 --> 10:37.386
I got a gaggle of nephews
who need to get fed now.

10:37.387 --> 10:38.720
I'm taking 'em tumblin'.

10:38.721 --> 10:41.181
- Nephews, you love tumbling, yes or no?
- Yes!

10:41.182 --> 10:43.308
See, that's the difference
between them and me.

10:43.309 --> 10:48.814
I do not like tumblin'. Especially
if I'm tumbling 13 picks. Feel me?

10:48.815 --> 10:50.190
<i>Seventh pick...</i>

10:50.191 --> 10:52.238
Listen, I appreciate that,
Vontae, I really do.

10:52.360 --> 10:54.153
- But I gotta go.
<i>- Seventeen or 18...</i>

10:54.154 --> 10:55.871
<i>Then I got tax...</i>

11:07.125 --> 11:08.292
Y'all ready to go?

11:08.293 --> 11:09.376
Yes!

11:09.377 --> 11:11.170
- Y'all ready to tumble?
- Yes!

11:11.171 --> 11:12.421
- Yes?
- Yes!

11:12.422 --> 11:14.299
That's what I want!

11:20.305 --> 11:21.388
<i>Hello?</i>

11:21.389 --> 11:23.223
Sonny. Earl Jennings.

11:23.224 --> 11:26.102
- Hey, Earl. You're with your boy today?
- <i>Yeah.</i>

11:26.436 --> 11:28.395
You guys in the Big Apple?

11:28.396 --> 11:30.647
<i>Listen, Sonny.</i>

11:30.648 --> 11:33.358
It's none of my business who
you draft today, all right?

11:33.359 --> 11:36.487
Ray will play for
whoever wants him.

11:36.571 --> 11:38.906
But if you're thinkin'
of pickin' him...

11:38.907 --> 11:41.283
I need you to know that
I raised Ray right.

11:41.284 --> 11:43.744
C'mon, Earl. I know
what the papers say.

11:43.745 --> 11:46.213
<i>I'll have him explain it to you.</i>

11:46.247 --> 11:47.915
<i>What's goin' on, Mr. Weaver?</i>

11:47.916 --> 11:48.957
<i>First of all,</i>

11:48.958 --> 11:51.168
I'm not in a gang.

11:51.169 --> 11:53.462
The guys that were with
me, I grew up with them,

11:53.463 --> 11:55.756
I've known 'em since I was a kid.

11:55.757 --> 11:58.884
But the dudes we ran into,

11:58.885 --> 12:02.304
they were big dudes,
and they came at us.

12:02.305 --> 12:04.264
What was I supposed to
do, just stand there?

12:04.265 --> 12:06.558
Well, they say you whooped
on that kid pretty good, Ray.

12:06.559 --> 12:07.935
He's still in the hospital.

12:07.936 --> 12:09.394
<i>He's not a kid.</i>

12:09.395 --> 12:11.980
None of 'em were.
They were grown men.

12:11.981 --> 12:13.482
They should have known
better, Mr. Weaver.

12:13.483 --> 12:16.068
Well, that's not the point.

12:16.069 --> 12:17.866
Did you hurt your hands?

12:19.572 --> 12:20.864
<i>You need your hands, Ray.</i>

12:20.865 --> 12:22.537
I know.

12:24.327 --> 12:26.170
I just lost my head.

12:26.621 --> 12:28.122
<i>Did you find it?</i>

12:28.831 --> 12:30.165
Yes, sir.

12:30.166 --> 12:33.001
Well, good. Now hold on
to it, you understand me?

12:33.002 --> 12:34.503
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

12:35.338 --> 12:37.214
Enjoy today, Ray.

12:37.215 --> 12:39.424
You only get drafted once.

12:39.425 --> 12:41.927
Yes, sir. I appreciate
that, Mr. Weaver.

12:49.852 --> 12:51.695
Ah...

12:51.771 --> 12:53.648
Jesus...

12:54.232 --> 12:56.817
What? What'd he say?

12:58.736 --> 13:02.489
I just wanna be a Brown.
Like you, Pop.

13:02.490 --> 13:05.243
Yeah, I want that, too.

13:05.285 --> 13:09.079
But you'll play where you play.
That's the way it works.

13:09.080 --> 13:10.789
I know.

13:10.790 --> 13:13.088
I'm just nervous, man.

13:13.960 --> 13:17.087
You see that? That's
the Dungeon Drop.

13:17.088 --> 13:19.673
Kids waited an hour to take it.

13:19.674 --> 13:23.593
It's exactly 50 feet from the end
of the slide right into the pool.

13:23.594 --> 13:25.137
Huge splash.

13:25.138 --> 13:26.763
Anybody within shouting distance

13:26.764 --> 13:28.598
would've gotten completely soaked.

13:28.599 --> 13:30.767
And people pay for that.

13:30.768 --> 13:34.187
I need you to make a splash,
Sonny. We need to sell tickets.

13:34.188 --> 13:37.316
Well, I'm trying to help you do
that, Anthony, in my own way.

13:37.317 --> 13:39.443
You can help me, by
makin' a splash.

13:39.444 --> 13:42.738
And if you can't do it,
then I have to do it, and...

13:45.283 --> 13:48.832
I don't wanna have
to do that, Sonny.

13:50.496 --> 13:53.590
Just to be clear here, you're
threatening to fire me, right?

13:55.501 --> 13:57.544
Let's talk about the Draft.

13:57.545 --> 13:59.297
What do we need?

13:59.422 --> 14:02.799
I hear a quarterback is
a good thing to have.

14:02.800 --> 14:05.135
- We have Brian Drew.
- Well...

14:05.136 --> 14:08.221
Word on Drew is that he's weak in
the knees. That's what I heard.

14:08.222 --> 14:09.514
Well, that's because
you heard it from me.

14:09.515 --> 14:10.974
We were 6-and-10 last season.

14:10.975 --> 14:13.185
We were 5-and-1 until
Drew went down.

14:13.186 --> 14:16.485
And he went down because
he's weak in the knees.

14:19.233 --> 14:21.693
There's not a quarterback in
this draft after Callahan

14:21.694 --> 14:24.446
that can make a difference
to our team, all right?

14:24.447 --> 14:26.114
And we're way too far
down to get him.

14:26.115 --> 14:27.616
Okay, okay. What else?

14:27.617 --> 14:28.950
Our shiny new head coach

14:28.951 --> 14:31.203
wants a shiny new running back.

14:31.204 --> 14:34.127
Ray Jennings. He's
Cleveland royalty.

14:34.415 --> 14:36.713
I know what Penn wants.

14:36.793 --> 14:38.752
Come on, Anthony, you said
you would stay out of this.

14:38.753 --> 14:40.712
Coach Penn has a Super Bowl ring.

14:40.713 --> 14:42.214
He used to coach the
Cowboys, you know?

14:42.215 --> 14:43.924
He took over for a team
that won the Super Bowl

14:43.925 --> 14:45.926
and then proceeded to
run it into the ground.

14:45.927 --> 14:48.225
Got himself fired. Lucky for us.

14:48.388 --> 14:51.311
The Cowboys really
have great helmets.

14:51.557 --> 14:55.982
Well, Anthony, you're the owner. You
can change the helmets if you want.

14:56.145 --> 14:59.064
Look, you just gotta let me
do my job. I mean...

15:00.650 --> 15:04.654
I like Vontae Mack.
He's special. He's different.

15:04.904 --> 15:07.197
He could transform our
defense. Even as a rookie.

15:07.198 --> 15:10.201
Defense doesn't make a splash.

15:12.662 --> 15:14.584
Sonny.

15:17.667 --> 15:20.010
People pay to get wet.

15:21.712 --> 15:23.004
<i>Shameful.</i>

15:23.005 --> 15:25.507
<i>You're almost glad Coach
Weaver isn't around</i>

15:25.508 --> 15:28.218
<i>to watch his son run this
team into the ground.</i>

15:28.219 --> 15:29.344
<i>I mean, Tone, listen,</i>

15:29.345 --> 15:33.265
<i>this guy comes two years after
supposedly saving San Francisco</i>

15:33.266 --> 15:35.934
<i>and general manages us
right to a losing season.</i>

15:35.935 --> 15:40.564
<i>Then you follow that up the next
season by firing his own father.</i>

15:40.565 --> 15:43.859
<i>Coach Weaver, rest his soul.
Tone, he was football in...</i>

15:49.782 --> 15:52.576
- Have we tried everyone?
- Everyone worth asking.

15:52.577 --> 15:55.375
So far, no one's
willin' to overpay.

15:55.538 --> 15:57.210
Shit.

15:57.373 --> 15:59.958
I really thought I could
get Sonny Weaver to bite.

15:59.959 --> 16:01.501
I mean, he just lost his old man...

16:10.303 --> 16:12.020
Fleece him.

16:15.057 --> 16:18.060
Sonny! How can I help you?

16:19.979 --> 16:22.731
Okay. I'm ready to do this, Tom.

16:22.732 --> 16:29.080
Our next two number one picks and a
third-rounder for your pick today.

16:29.238 --> 16:32.616
Correction. Your next
three first-round picks.

16:32.617 --> 16:33.742
<i>What?</i>

16:33.743 --> 16:35.335
You heard me.

16:40.416 --> 16:41.583
You want me to give you

16:41.584 --> 16:44.586
the Cleveland Browns' first-round
picks for the next three years?

16:44.587 --> 16:45.962
That's right.

16:45.963 --> 16:48.131
Well, that's insane, Tom. That...

16:48.132 --> 16:49.591
That wasn't your offer.

16:49.592 --> 16:51.301
<i>Well, I changed my offer.</i>

16:51.302 --> 16:52.886
<i>Hell, we live in a different world</i>

16:52.887 --> 16:54.429
<i>than we did a couple of hours ago.</i>

16:54.430 --> 16:57.265
<i>I made you a fair offer and you
told me to enjoy my pancakes.</i>

16:57.266 --> 16:59.976
You think I'm gonna give you my
next three number one picks?

16:59.977 --> 17:02.562
<i>You're panickin', Sonny, and I
intend to take advantage of that.</i>

17:04.190 --> 17:06.112
I'm not panicking.

17:06.150 --> 17:10.530
Your next three first-round
picks. Yes or no?

17:17.453 --> 17:19.626
<i>You still there, Sonny?</i>

17:27.630 --> 17:29.339
It's fourth and forever.

17:29.340 --> 17:31.424
I'm talking fourth
and, like, miles.

17:31.425 --> 17:34.761
Fourth down and 26
yards to go, okay?

17:34.762 --> 17:36.429
Everybody's dropped back deep.

17:36.430 --> 17:38.181
Their safeties are
halfway to Abilene,

17:38.182 --> 17:40.225
thinkin' they got this thing iced.

17:40.226 --> 17:43.144
Everybody and their mother,
hell, their grandmothers,

17:43.145 --> 17:46.648
think it's gonna be the deep ball,
the Long Bomb, the Hail Mary.

17:46.649 --> 17:50.819
Instead, it's a toss out
to my man Ray Jennings.

17:50.820 --> 17:51.945
And then, boom!

17:51.946 --> 17:55.156
He gets swallowed up by this
huge, ugly nose tackle.

17:55.157 --> 17:56.992
The Hee-ha or the Ho-ha.

17:58.160 --> 17:59.828
One of those huge
Samoan kids, right?

17:59.829 --> 18:01.871
And when he looks down,
guess what he sees?

18:01.872 --> 18:03.498
Nothin'. 'Cause Ray ain't there.

18:03.499 --> 18:04.708
You know where Ray is?

18:04.709 --> 18:09.546
He teleported six feet to the
left and he's off to the races.

18:09.547 --> 18:11.840
Every poor Sooner
bastard on the field

18:11.841 --> 18:14.050
is soilin' his Pampers
tryin' to get to him.

18:14.051 --> 18:17.012
What does Ray do?
He brings it back! He cuts!

18:17.013 --> 18:20.932
Shimmy, shake-n-bake, and
hurdles over Kyle Danforth.

18:20.933 --> 18:23.393
All-American Kyle
Danforth and he's ghost.

18:23.394 --> 18:24.603
He's a good player.

18:24.604 --> 18:27.939
67 yards. Touchdown. Ballgame.

18:27.940 --> 18:29.524
I'm telling you guys.

18:29.525 --> 18:31.776
Ray's dad was a special
player for the Browns,

18:31.777 --> 18:33.862
but this kid might be even better.

18:33.863 --> 18:35.238
'Morning, Sonny.

18:35.239 --> 18:36.698
Good morning, guys.

18:36.699 --> 18:38.450
Was just tellin' Jelly
Doughnut and the guys

18:38.451 --> 18:40.076
my favorite Ray Jennings story

18:40.077 --> 18:43.456
'cause they're tellin' me
we have not yet decided.

18:43.748 --> 18:46.750
I mean, we're not seriously
considering anybody else, right?

18:46.751 --> 18:48.423
What are you doing, Sonny?

18:50.796 --> 18:52.589
I just made a trade
with the Seahawks.

18:52.590 --> 18:54.342
For?

18:57.637 --> 18:59.389
The number one pick.

18:59.472 --> 19:01.269
Oh!

19:03.768 --> 19:06.645
You got us Bo Callahan?

19:06.646 --> 19:08.938
Certainly appears that way.

19:08.939 --> 19:10.231
Ali, you here?

19:10.232 --> 19:11.733
Yes.

19:12.234 --> 19:14.903
Is this gonna screw us
up with the salary cap?

19:14.904 --> 19:17.072
Moving from seven to one?

19:17.073 --> 19:19.032
It's about another $1.5 million

19:19.033 --> 19:20.450
we weren't anticipating
for this year.

19:20.451 --> 19:23.625
Maybe an extra $5.5
million in signing bonus.

19:23.829 --> 19:25.626
We have that?

19:25.665 --> 19:27.123
We can make it work.

19:27.124 --> 19:29.126
Let me get into it.

19:31.170 --> 19:33.588
- Pretty good news, huh?
- Yeah!

19:33.589 --> 19:35.591
Number one pick?

19:37.093 --> 19:40.187
Pretty big! That's great!

19:44.767 --> 19:47.268
I thought we had a QB.

19:47.269 --> 19:49.487
Tell me, what did we give up?

19:50.356 --> 19:52.483
A number one pick this year?

19:52.692 --> 19:54.193
And?

19:54.985 --> 19:56.611
First-round pick next year.

19:56.612 --> 19:58.279
Okay, well, that's a lot, but
when you get a chance at

19:58.280 --> 19:59.781
a player like Callahan...

19:59.782 --> 20:01.825
And the year after that.

20:01.826 --> 20:03.623
Three number ones?

20:04.203 --> 20:07.288
You gave up three
consecutive first-rounders?

20:07.289 --> 20:09.624
Sonny, that's our future.

20:09.625 --> 20:10.875
No.

20:10.876 --> 20:13.049
Bo Callahan's our future.

20:13.504 --> 20:15.677
$30 million, Sonny.

20:16.132 --> 20:17.215
Excuse me?

20:17.216 --> 20:18.508
$30 million.

20:18.509 --> 20:20.218
That's what you're paying
me to coach this team

20:20.219 --> 20:21.553
for the next six years.

20:21.554 --> 20:24.806
Did it cross your mind, did you
think it might be maybe important

20:24.807 --> 20:27.401
to discuss this
decision with me first?

20:28.144 --> 20:29.394
No.

20:29.395 --> 20:31.647
It's my call.

20:34.483 --> 20:36.484
As you can infer from
Coach Peon's reaction,

20:36.485 --> 20:38.828
I just put all our
asses on the line

20:39.655 --> 20:43.455
for a kid I think we all
agree is pretty good.

20:43.993 --> 20:45.618
Until about 10 minutes ago,

20:45.619 --> 20:47.495
I don't think any of us
thought this was possible,

20:47.496 --> 20:49.664
and I seriously doubt that we have

20:49.665 --> 20:52.167
looked at him the
way we might have.

20:52.168 --> 20:55.378
That's my fault. All right,
guys? That's on me.

20:55.379 --> 20:58.506
Now that's changed. So if
we go ahead with this,

20:58.507 --> 21:00.341
if we pick him, and
find out tomorrow

21:00.342 --> 21:04.012
that he has got knee problems,
he's got bedwetting problems,

21:04.013 --> 21:07.015
or he's got goddamn OCD,
we're all gonna be fired.

21:07.016 --> 21:08.984
What's beeping?

21:10.352 --> 21:11.519
<i>Hello?</i>

21:11.520 --> 21:13.943
Am I on the big phone?

21:14.023 --> 21:17.026
<i>Yes, Anthony, you're
on the big phone.</i>

21:17.568 --> 21:19.866
And can everybody hear me?

21:20.029 --> 21:21.279
Good morning, Mr. Molina.

21:21.280 --> 21:22.906
We can hear you.

21:22.948 --> 21:26.034
Sonny! I'd like to
congratulate you.

21:26.035 --> 21:29.379
I asked you to make a
splash and you did.

21:30.372 --> 21:32.081
Is everybody still there?

21:32.082 --> 21:34.709
Anthony, how do you
already know about this?

21:34.710 --> 21:37.212
What can I tell you, my boy?
It's good to be the owner.

21:37.213 --> 21:40.216
I'm about to board my plane.
I'm headin' for New York.

21:40.382 --> 21:41.883
You're going to the Draft?

21:41.884 --> 21:44.219
No, I'm gonna see <i>Spider-Man,
Turn Off the Dark.</i>

21:44.220 --> 21:47.931
Of course I'm going to the
Draft! We got Bo Callahan!

21:47.932 --> 21:49.224
Is that it?

21:49.225 --> 21:50.726
Yes, sir.

21:52.478 --> 21:53.603
Good.

21:53.604 --> 21:55.396
Anthony? Anthony?

21:55.397 --> 21:58.316
Sonny, my assistant Heather just
arrived from the equipment manager.

21:58.317 --> 22:00.568
I had a jersey made
up for the young man.

22:00.569 --> 22:04.239
I'm gonna hand it to him myself
personally when his name is announced.

22:04.240 --> 22:07.116
Bo Callahan's gonna be
the son I never had.

22:07.117 --> 22:08.743
Anthony, you already have a son.

22:08.744 --> 22:10.917
Sonny, nice work!

22:12.248 --> 22:15.166
Well, I guess that's settled.

22:15.167 --> 22:17.502
Yeah. It may be.

22:17.503 --> 22:19.629
We're still gonna have to
take another look at this kid

22:19.630 --> 22:21.339
and everything there
is to know about him

22:21.340 --> 22:23.808
before I can feel good
about what we just risked.

22:24.093 --> 22:25.970
Meaning all of our jobs?

22:27.763 --> 22:30.181
Yes. I do understand
how important it is,

22:30.182 --> 22:31.766
but Mr. Weaver is
not here right now.

22:31.767 --> 22:35.186
So the best I can do is, I can leave
him a message and get back to you.

22:35.187 --> 22:36.729
Oh, you know, he
actually just walked in.

22:36.730 --> 22:38.189
Can you hold for one
moment, please?

22:38.190 --> 22:41.276
- Where's Ali?
- I don't know where Ali is.

22:41.277 --> 22:43.361
She's not in her office. Ali!

22:43.362 --> 22:45.114
I'm right here.

22:46.657 --> 22:48.366
What's he doing here?

22:48.367 --> 22:50.785
This is Rick. He's a new intern.

22:50.786 --> 22:52.662
Yeah. We've met before, actually.

22:52.663 --> 22:54.622
He'll be helping you today
because Rhona got mono.

22:54.623 --> 22:58.126
I need Keith and Jeremy for
salary cap troubleshooting, so...

22:58.127 --> 23:01.504
Um, I have Adam Schefter from ESPN
on the line. He heard a rumor.

23:01.505 --> 23:04.507
Oh, great. Tell Schefter to
stick his rumor up his...

23:04.508 --> 23:06.225
Sonny...

23:07.970 --> 23:11.306
All right. Then tell him I'm not
taking any media calls right now.

23:11.307 --> 23:12.390
Yes, sir.

23:12.391 --> 23:14.017
And what kind of soda did you want?

23:14.018 --> 23:15.643
I don't want a goddamn soda, Rich!

23:15.644 --> 23:17.646
Don't yell at him. Thank you, Rick.

23:21.191 --> 23:23.151
Listen, I know you're mad.

23:23.152 --> 23:24.995
I'm not mad.

23:27.072 --> 23:29.032
- And I'm sorry about the thing this morning.
- I'm not mad.

23:29.033 --> 23:31.200
I understand the situation.

23:31.201 --> 23:32.452
Whatever it is that you and I have,

23:32.453 --> 23:34.495
you've been very clear
that it wasn't...

23:34.496 --> 23:38.250
What are you talkin' about, "clear"?
I haven't been clear about anything.

23:39.251 --> 23:40.843
Well...

23:41.378 --> 23:43.676
Maybe that's the problem.

23:48.844 --> 23:52.518
So, what did you have to give
up for the number one pick?

23:56.185 --> 23:58.561
The first-round pick for
the next three years.

23:58.562 --> 24:00.605
- Wow.
- Yeah, "wow."

24:00.606 --> 24:03.274
The other one, you goat!
Get your head outta your ass!

24:03.275 --> 24:04.525
What's going on?

24:04.526 --> 24:05.735
Who the hell is this moron?

24:05.736 --> 24:07.570
This is our new intern, Rick.
What do you want?

24:07.571 --> 24:08.988
I need every tape of Callahan.

24:08.989 --> 24:10.198
I have a call for Mr. Weaver.

24:10.199 --> 24:12.533
And suddenly, every tape
of everyone is AWOL

24:12.534 --> 24:13.826
and shit-show Johnny over here

24:13.827 --> 24:15.536
doesn't have a goddamn
clue where they are!

24:15.537 --> 24:17.580
Game tape is in the
archives. Chill out.

24:17.581 --> 24:19.540
Chill out? They changed
the punch code!

24:19.541 --> 24:22.251
Okay. I will get it, okay?
I will get the Callahan tapes.

24:22.252 --> 24:23.378
For Christ sakes!

24:23.379 --> 24:25.421
Just deal with the call
and handle lunch orders.

24:25.422 --> 24:27.423
Don't ever speak to an
intern like that again.

24:27.424 --> 24:29.926
Go back in the war room. Your
tapes will be here shortly.

24:29.927 --> 24:31.804
Uh, Mr. Weaver.

24:32.179 --> 24:33.304
What?

24:33.305 --> 24:35.933
Chris Crawford is on line three.

24:36.517 --> 24:37.558
Crawford!

24:37.559 --> 24:39.394
<i>How's my favorite super-agent?</i>

24:39.395 --> 24:41.270
I'm livin' the dream, Sonny Weave.

24:41.271 --> 24:43.898
Dreamin' of a magical
wonderland called Cleveland

24:43.899 --> 24:45.733
where my golden-armed quarterback

24:45.734 --> 24:48.027
is gonna make all your
dreams come true.

24:48.028 --> 24:50.113
Yeah. How is my favorite Badger?

24:50.114 --> 24:52.490
<i>He's doing great. He's excited.</i>

24:52.491 --> 24:54.826
You know, Bo loves Coach Penn.

24:54.827 --> 24:57.079
He loves the Dawg Pound.

24:57.913 --> 25:01.249
And did I mention that Bo loves
playin' in the cold weather?

25:01.250 --> 25:03.793
'Cause Bo loves playin'
in the cold weather.

25:03.794 --> 25:05.503
And we both know it's
cold in Cleveland.

25:05.504 --> 25:07.588
<i>I'd love to talk with him, Chris.</i>

25:07.589 --> 25:09.841
He's right here. Hold on.

25:10.426 --> 25:12.599
Sonny Weaver. Cleveland.

25:16.432 --> 25:18.099
How are you, Mr. Weaver?

25:18.100 --> 25:20.810
I'm doin' fine. How are
you, son? Excited?

25:20.811 --> 25:24.110
Well, of course I am.
It's an excitin' day. I can't lie.

25:24.440 --> 25:27.525
Good, good. Well, try and
enjoy this part if you can.

25:27.526 --> 25:29.694
<i>You only get drafted once.</i>

25:29.695 --> 25:32.030
Well, thank you very much,
sir. I appreciate that.

25:32.031 --> 25:33.114
Got a question for you, Bo.

25:33.115 --> 25:35.458
Anything, Mr. Weaver. Fire away.

25:36.201 --> 25:38.624
How important is winning to you?

25:38.954 --> 25:40.455
Excuse me?

25:41.498 --> 25:42.874
Well, I've seen all the tape on you

25:42.875 --> 25:44.208
and talked to everyone
that matters,

25:44.209 --> 25:46.544
but that's the thing
I still don't know.

25:46.545 --> 25:49.298
<i>How important is winning to you?</i>

25:49.798 --> 25:52.471
Well, winning is everything, sir.

25:54.678 --> 25:56.888
Everyone says that, Bo.

25:56.889 --> 25:59.357
I suppose they do, sir.

25:59.475 --> 26:01.809
<i>Look, I don't know
what else to tell you.</i>

26:01.810 --> 26:04.904
<i>Winning is the only thing
that matters to me.</i>

26:07.983 --> 26:11.402
Oh, and by the way, I'd like to offer
my condolences for your father.

26:11.403 --> 26:13.863
Thanks, Bo. Thanks for saying that.

26:13.864 --> 26:15.656
Thank Chris for me.

26:15.657 --> 26:17.075
Talk to you later, pal.

26:17.076 --> 26:19.327
Okay. Thank you, Mr. Weaver.

26:19.328 --> 26:21.120
Look forward to meetin' you, sir.

26:23.832 --> 26:24.916
Great job.

26:24.917 --> 26:26.000
Was I all right?

26:26.001 --> 26:28.219
- Cleveland! Yeah.
- Cleveland.

26:31.340 --> 26:32.841
Thank you.

26:35.552 --> 26:36.677
Ali?

26:42.017 --> 26:43.689
Great.

26:46.355 --> 26:47.396
Hi, Mom.

26:47.397 --> 26:50.566
You sold a cow for magic beans.

26:50.567 --> 26:52.026
<i>What?</i>

26:52.027 --> 26:54.737
You could have stole
Ray Jennings at seven!

26:54.738 --> 26:57.698
How does the entire world
already know about this, Mom?

26:57.699 --> 27:00.034
Because Vontae Mack
just tweeted it.

27:00.035 --> 27:01.369
He tweeted it?

27:02.538 --> 27:04.539
Yeah. Here.

27:04.540 --> 27:08.709
"Agent just called. Browns
trade for number one.

27:08.710 --> 27:12.922
<i>"Sorry, Cleve.
You get Bo, no Vontae.</i>

27:12.923 --> 27:15.551
<i>"Dumb move."</i>

27:15.884 --> 27:17.556
You're on Twitter?

27:17.970 --> 27:19.562
You're not?

27:19.638 --> 27:23.062
I'm sorry, Sonny.
Is this a bad time?

27:23.725 --> 27:25.726
I gotta go, Mom.

27:25.727 --> 27:28.229
This is the Draft Analysis
we've all been working on

27:28.230 --> 27:29.272
for the last two months.

27:29.273 --> 27:31.821
Fire! Ali! Fire!

27:31.900 --> 27:33.901
- Ali! Fire!
- Did you hear that?

27:33.902 --> 27:36.780
I'm coming. God!

27:45.122 --> 27:47.331
Can I get you gentlemen
some coffee?

27:47.332 --> 27:48.416
Love some.

27:48.417 --> 27:49.959
Light and sweet, honey. Thanks.

27:49.960 --> 27:52.758
Yeah, I'm not getting
you idiots anything.

27:54.006 --> 27:58.134
I like her. Little Miss Salary Cap.
She's a sweetheart.

27:58.135 --> 27:59.260
Yeah, she's the best.

27:59.261 --> 28:01.434
Why am I here, Sonny?

28:01.513 --> 28:03.431
Because Molina thinks you
coached the Cowboys.

28:03.432 --> 28:04.807
I did coach the Cowboys.

28:04.808 --> 28:07.356
And I think you were
a bad babysitter.

28:09.479 --> 28:12.315
You know, my wife loved
livin' in Dallas, Sonny.

28:12.316 --> 28:14.108
It's a rich town
full of fancy people

28:14.109 --> 28:15.943
and she likes that kind of thing.

28:15.944 --> 28:18.029
So she wasn't exactly
thrilled when I said,

28:18.030 --> 28:21.699
"Hey, baby, pack your bags.
We're moving to Cleveland."

28:21.700 --> 28:23.618
Well, there's fancy
people here, too.

28:23.619 --> 28:24.994
No.

28:24.995 --> 28:27.496
There's really not.
Which is okay by me.

28:27.497 --> 28:29.874
But I dragged my pretty
wife to this town

28:29.875 --> 28:32.084
because this city
deserves a championship

28:32.085 --> 28:34.503
and I'm the guy that
can deliver it.

28:34.504 --> 28:35.588
Well, then we're on
the same page, Vince.

28:35.589 --> 28:36.672
Oh, yeah?

28:36.673 --> 28:38.174
Then keep me in the loop.

28:38.175 --> 28:40.009
There is no loop. All right?

28:40.010 --> 28:42.762
There's me doing my
job, you doing yours.

28:42.763 --> 28:44.222
Your job is to coach
the team I give you.

28:44.223 --> 28:45.473
They do it different in Dallas?

28:45.474 --> 28:49.103
Yeah, they do. They win. A lot.

28:50.562 --> 28:53.648
I had my choice of teams to coach,
Sonny, and I chose this team, okay?

28:53.649 --> 28:56.067
I chose to coach this team.

28:56.068 --> 28:58.903
Not the team you're puttin'
together in your head, on the fly

28:58.904 --> 29:00.655
'cause your old man died last week

29:00.656 --> 29:02.829
and you're tapping
one of your execs.

29:03.408 --> 29:04.992
What did you just say?

29:04.993 --> 29:07.871
I'm sorry. Is that
supposed to be a secret?

29:09.665 --> 29:14.090
You know, around here, we called
my "old man" Coach Weaver.

29:14.544 --> 29:17.421
And yes, my father died last week.

29:17.422 --> 29:19.173
So the next time you
refer to his name,

29:19.174 --> 29:20.841
next time you say it, at
least, in front of me,

29:20.842 --> 29:24.846
you say it with some goddamn
reverence, because he earned it.

29:25.681 --> 29:27.228
Fair enough?

29:30.686 --> 29:33.780
Keep your legs up now.

29:33.855 --> 29:36.274
Don't even think about it.

29:41.113 --> 29:42.910
Sonny Weaver Jr.

29:43.031 --> 29:44.748
<i>Vontae.</i>

29:45.534 --> 29:47.451
I'm disappointed in
you, Mr. Weaver.

29:47.452 --> 29:48.577
Let me tell you something, Vontae,

29:48.578 --> 29:49.704
and I don't have a lot of time,

29:49.705 --> 29:52.299
so I want you to listen
to me carefully, okay?

29:52.541 --> 29:54.375
- Are you listening?
<i>- Yeah.</i>

29:54.376 --> 29:55.876
Don't Twitter.

29:55.877 --> 29:58.546
For the love of Jesus, just stop.

29:58.547 --> 30:02.508
Delete your profile. Get off the web.
Do not do this to yourself.

30:02.509 --> 30:04.260
I don't know why you
care what I do.

30:04.261 --> 30:06.220
I can do whatever I want. Right?

30:06.221 --> 30:07.888
Of course you can, Vontae,

30:07.889 --> 30:09.473
but every GM in the league
has now read your tweet,

30:09.474 --> 30:11.642
or whatever they call them,

30:11.643 --> 30:13.894
and they've all made a mental
note that Vontae Mack,

30:13.895 --> 30:17.565
however prodigiously talented, is a
guy who likes to talk, all right?

30:17.566 --> 30:19.066
Who likes to spread rumors,

30:19.067 --> 30:20.735
who's more than willing
to announce to the world

30:20.736 --> 30:24.456
any inane thought that
passes through his head.

30:24.823 --> 30:26.365
