Manager called the
cops when somebody

45:49.121 --> 45:51.581
broke in his office
and stole some money.

45:51.582 --> 45:53.667
Of course, none of
this is Bo's fault.

45:53.668 --> 45:55.418
'Course.

45:55.419 --> 45:56.920
But...

45:57.171 --> 46:01.591
But the cops came and they took
everybody's name regardless.

46:01.592 --> 46:05.220
It was a few hundred people.
Standard operating procedure.

46:05.221 --> 46:06.722
But...

46:08.599 --> 46:10.684
Ask me who wasn't there.

46:10.685 --> 46:12.686
Who wasn't there, Ralph?

46:12.687 --> 46:14.860
Any of his teammates.

46:16.190 --> 46:20.285
None of his teammates came to the
poor guy's birthday party, Sonny.

46:32.790 --> 46:33.957
Dick Moore.

46:33.958 --> 46:36.376
<i>Hey, Coach. Sonny Weaver.</i>

46:36.377 --> 46:39.254
You're about to be
a very happy man.

46:39.255 --> 46:42.257
Bo Callahan's some
of my finest work.

46:42.258 --> 46:44.217
What can you tell me about him?

46:44.218 --> 46:48.054
I can tell you what I just told
you, he's some of my finest work.

46:48.055 --> 46:49.556
Anything else?

46:49.557 --> 46:51.274
You have the tapes.

46:51.392 --> 46:53.601
He's the real deal, Sonny.

46:53.602 --> 46:56.230
Don't overthink this like
your dad would have.

46:56.480 --> 46:58.482
<i>No offense.</i>

46:58.899 --> 47:01.276
<i>Look. I love Bo.</i>

47:01.319 --> 47:03.153
My coaches love him.

47:03.154 --> 47:05.322
The cheerleaders love him.
The fans love him.

47:05.323 --> 47:07.574
<i>Everyone loves him.</i>

47:07.575 --> 47:10.794
Then how come none of his teammates
went to his birthday party?

47:12.330 --> 47:14.673
Are you kiddin' me with this?

47:14.832 --> 47:17.167
Seems relevant.

47:17.168 --> 47:19.586
You want to tear this
kid down, or what?

47:19.587 --> 47:22.089
No, I'd just like your take on it.

47:22.173 --> 47:24.090
I find it odd that
nobody on the team

47:24.091 --> 47:26.760
was at their teammate's
21st birthday party.

47:26.761 --> 47:30.430
I don't know, Sonny. What do
you think's more plausible?

47:30.431 --> 47:32.766
That nobody on an 85-person squad

47:32.767 --> 47:35.645
attended a party
thrown by the captain?

47:35.686 --> 47:37.854
Or could it be that when
the cops got to the place

47:37.855 --> 47:40.899
and realized that my boys
had done nothin' wrong,

47:40.900 --> 47:43.360
decided not to take down
any of the players' names

47:43.361 --> 47:44.444
because they didn't wanna jam up

47:44.445 --> 47:47.039
a bunch of good kids
for doin' nothin'?

47:48.657 --> 47:51.125
<i>Oh, wait. Wait a minute.</i>

47:51.285 --> 47:53.128
Your theory seems right.

47:53.537 --> 47:55.129
Bo Callahan.

47:55.373 --> 47:59.719
Bo Callahan hasn't got any friends.

48:00.044 --> 48:02.296
Good luck with the Draft today.

48:03.214 --> 48:05.842
C'mon, you guys. You're
lookin' pathetic.

48:41.335 --> 48:42.669
Hey, Max.

48:42.670 --> 48:45.172
Hey, Sonny. Hope you're holdin' up.

48:45.381 --> 48:47.599
I got an offer for number one.

48:47.716 --> 48:50.685
Yeah? Well, I'm all ears.
What do you have in mind?

48:50.886 --> 48:52.429
Okay, here's what we got.

48:52.430 --> 48:55.181
Maurice Castillo, Antonio Taylor,

48:55.182 --> 48:58.268
our first-rounder next year
and the year after that.

48:58.269 --> 49:00.728
<i>That's two number ones,
a blue-chip running back...</i>

49:00.729 --> 49:02.355
I know who they are, Max.

49:02.356 --> 49:04.779
Then you know it's a fair offer.

49:08.404 --> 49:09.905
I'm intrigued.

49:11.365 --> 49:13.708
Good. Let's make a deal.

49:14.452 --> 49:16.703
- Well, you gotta give me some time.
- Time?

49:16.704 --> 49:19.414
Sonny, time's one thing
neither one of us have.

49:19.415 --> 49:20.623
Make the deal.

49:20.624 --> 49:22.216
Give me an hour.

49:22.877 --> 49:24.970
We'll give you half that.

49:31.635 --> 49:32.927
What's up?

49:32.928 --> 49:35.138
I just got off the
phone with Max Stone.

49:35.139 --> 49:37.557
Yeah? How are things in Buffalo?

49:37.558 --> 49:39.058
Well, I guess you
didn't ask him then,

49:39.059 --> 49:41.186
when you called him behind my back.

49:41.353 --> 49:42.812
Max is an old friend of mine.

49:42.813 --> 49:45.440
He calls me up to congratulate
us on the Callahan thing

49:45.441 --> 49:47.609
and I express my
opinions on the matter.

49:47.610 --> 49:49.908
He call you, or you call him?

49:50.070 --> 49:52.405
It's such a crazy day.
Who remembers?

49:52.406 --> 49:53.865
Yeah, well, how 'bout
try and remember this,

49:53.866 --> 49:56.493
I can and I will fire your ass.

49:56.494 --> 49:57.995
Then do it, Sonny.

50:02.750 --> 50:04.083
You actually think
I'm gonna give up

50:04.084 --> 50:06.127
Bo Callahan for
Taylor and Castillo?

50:06.128 --> 50:08.171
Hmm? Maurice Castillo?

50:08.172 --> 50:09.672
And draft picks, okay?

50:09.673 --> 50:10.757
Don't forget the
draft picks, Sonny.

50:10.758 --> 50:13.056
You do remember what
those are, right?

50:15.137 --> 50:17.514
All right. Look. It's...

50:17.515 --> 50:19.599
On the surface, it's not
a terrible trade, but

50:19.600 --> 50:21.768
why do you think we
need to do this now?

50:21.769 --> 50:24.103
Because you burned up any currency
this team had this morning.

50:24.104 --> 50:25.980
Now you have the opportunity
to build it back up.

50:25.981 --> 50:27.607
And I don't know what your
problem is with Maurice.

50:27.608 --> 50:28.983
He's a beast.

50:28.984 --> 50:30.818
Looks like Tarzan, plays like Jane.

50:30.819 --> 50:32.779
Your opinion. He
plays in my system.

50:32.780 --> 50:33.821
He doesn't block!

50:33.822 --> 50:35.782
I don't need him to block.
I need him to run.

50:35.783 --> 50:37.700
Which he does, like
a bat outta hell.

50:37.701 --> 50:40.453
Which takes the pressure
off my offense, okay?

50:40.454 --> 50:45.050
I got 52 Tarzans in that locker
room. I could use a Jane.

50:48.879 --> 50:52.383
You should at least seriously
consider what I'm saying.

50:55.719 --> 50:59.013
All right. Get me the
numbers on all their guys.

50:59.014 --> 51:00.807
We got about 25 minutes
to see what's what.

51:00.808 --> 51:02.275
Great.

51:12.861 --> 51:14.946
Mr. Molina. How are you?

51:16.907 --> 51:19.075
Very good.

51:19.076 --> 51:21.544
Excellent. That's good.
Good to see you.

51:21.870 --> 51:23.667
I'll take you inside.

51:27.251 --> 51:28.877
Right up here.

51:30.421 --> 51:31.754
Sonny call you yet?

51:31.755 --> 51:33.172
Oh, not yet.

51:33.173 --> 51:34.215
What's he doing?

51:34.216 --> 51:35.925
Well, I'm sure he's
gonna call soon.

51:35.926 --> 51:38.678
These are our team reps.
This is Wyndham. This is Phil.

51:38.679 --> 51:40.513
- Mr. Anthony Molina.
- How do you do?

51:40.514 --> 51:42.348
- Sir.
- How do you do?

51:42.349 --> 51:43.516
Right up here.

51:43.517 --> 51:44.601
I'm not sitting here.

51:44.602 --> 51:45.685
Oh, no, of course you're not.

51:45.686 --> 51:47.604
You're with the Commissioner,
up in his lounge.

51:47.605 --> 51:50.699
Here, let me show you the way.
Let's go around here.

51:52.985 --> 51:54.702
He's even better.

51:55.029 --> 51:57.202
Mr. Commissioner?

51:57.239 --> 51:58.740
Hey, Anthony. How are you doing?

51:58.741 --> 52:00.908
What are you doing in my lounge?

52:00.909 --> 52:03.620
You guys sure made tonight
a lot more exciting.

52:03.621 --> 52:04.746
Thanks for inviting me in.

52:04.747 --> 52:05.955
Enjoy it. Good luck.

52:05.956 --> 52:07.582
- Will do.
- Okay.

52:07.583 --> 52:09.876
Can we talk football?

52:09.877 --> 52:11.711
Just football, for 30 seconds?

52:11.712 --> 52:13.464
We can always talk football.

52:15.966 --> 52:18.217
There's a deal on the
table from Buffalo.

52:18.218 --> 52:19.970
I heard.

52:21.055 --> 52:22.555
What's the war room think?

52:22.556 --> 52:24.182
Split.

52:24.475 --> 52:26.142
Penn wants me to do it.

52:26.143 --> 52:27.895
But you don't?

52:27.978 --> 52:29.062
I don't.

52:29.063 --> 52:30.229
Why?

52:30.230 --> 52:31.856
Because I know, in
my heart and my gut,

52:31.857 --> 52:33.399
that if I make this
trade with Buffalo,

52:33.400 --> 52:36.903
then I don't get to
make a pick this year.

52:36.904 --> 52:39.572
All I get back are
future draft picks

52:39.573 --> 52:42.997
for the guy that Molina
brings in to replace me.

52:45.829 --> 52:48.002
I've been here two years, Ali.

52:50.668 --> 52:52.590
Two years.

52:53.128 --> 52:55.797
I've never gotten a chance to

52:55.798 --> 52:58.926
see what a team I put
together can do out there.

53:00.678 --> 53:03.146
First year, it's my dad's team.

53:03.514 --> 53:06.766
Last year, Drew goes down
before I can see what we had.

53:06.767 --> 53:09.144
Then I get stuck with Penn,

53:09.937 --> 53:13.441
who I'm still trying to
figure out how to work with.

53:13.649 --> 53:16.948
This is finally supposed
to be my season.

53:18.487 --> 53:22.287
I just want the team
that I want. One time.

53:22.449 --> 53:25.577
So why are you bugging
me if you already know?

53:27.538 --> 53:29.460
I don't know.

53:34.294 --> 53:36.387
I'm makin' mistakes.

53:41.218 --> 53:43.219
Remember the '89 Super Bowl?

53:43.220 --> 53:45.472
49ers-Bengals.

53:46.056 --> 53:49.183
Niners down by three,
3:20 left in the game.

53:49.184 --> 53:53.312
93-yard winning drive, Taylor beats
the weak safety for a 10-yard TD.

53:53.313 --> 53:56.407
Yeah, but before the drive.

53:57.526 --> 54:00.820
Joe Montana's in the huddle. Right?

54:00.821 --> 54:02.780
<i>And unbelievably, somehow spots</i>

54:02.781 --> 54:04.824
<i>the actor John Candy in the stands.</i>

54:04.825 --> 54:07.827
He points at him and asks
the guys in the huddle,

54:07.828 --> 54:11.332
"Hey, isn't that John Candy?"

54:13.208 --> 54:15.668
They couldn't believe
the balls on him.

54:15.669 --> 54:19.093
To be that calm, in that
game, at that moment.

54:19.840 --> 54:24.015
His guys instantly
relax, they march...

54:24.178 --> 54:26.012
93 yards.

54:26.013 --> 54:28.431
93 yards.

54:28.432 --> 54:30.855
<i>Montana throws a little
slant to Taylor.</i>

54:32.102 --> 54:34.445
<i>49ers win the Super Bowl.</i>

54:34.772 --> 54:36.189
Great game.

54:36.190 --> 54:38.408
It was a great game.

54:45.115 --> 54:48.038
No one can stop a ticking clock.

54:48.368 --> 54:50.461
But the great ones,

54:51.038 --> 54:54.212
the great ones always find
a way to slow it down.

54:55.292 --> 54:58.045
So slow it down, Sonny.

55:01.256 --> 55:04.225
Okay. I made a decision.

55:04.551 --> 55:08.471
It's still Callahan. Let's
inform Buffalo that it's a no.

55:08.472 --> 55:10.224
That is beautiful.

55:10.265 --> 55:11.891
Okay, Sonny. We're with you.

55:11.892 --> 55:13.226
Like hell we are.

55:13.227 --> 55:16.062
All due respect, Sonny,
that is a bonehead move.

55:16.063 --> 55:18.564
Maybe so, but we're
back on Callahan.

55:18.565 --> 55:21.567
Do me a favor. Let's put up the
Wisconsin-Ohio State footage.

55:21.568 --> 55:22.735
Yeah, sure thing, Sonny.

55:22.736 --> 55:24.612
We've seen that footage,
like, two million times.

55:24.613 --> 55:27.031
What are you hopin' to find in
it that we haven't seen already?

55:27.032 --> 55:28.366
I'm just double-checking something.

55:28.367 --> 55:29.408
All right. Here we go.

55:29.409 --> 55:32.958
All right, roll it down to the
first time Vontae sacks Bo.

55:33.288 --> 55:35.131
All right. Here we go.

55:37.584 --> 55:40.294
Damn. He shook off two blockers
like they were rag dolls.

55:40.295 --> 55:41.754
And then Bo walks into a bear hug.

55:41.755 --> 55:43.130
Vontae wrapped him up pretty good.

55:43.131 --> 55:44.674
Yeah, Bo's hard to sack.

55:44.675 --> 55:47.473
He was one of the least-sacked
QBs in Division I last year.

55:47.594 --> 55:49.178
Go to the next play.

55:49.179 --> 55:50.596
The next sack?

55:50.597 --> 55:53.350
No. The next play after this one.

55:58.438 --> 55:59.856
What's he doing?

55:59.857 --> 56:03.359
He got flustered. Didn't wait
for the play to develop.

56:03.360 --> 56:04.944
Not Bo's finest moment.

56:04.945 --> 56:07.697
No. Whatever, it's one play.

56:07.698 --> 56:10.200
Take us down to Vontae's next sack.

56:12.911 --> 56:14.663
Ooh!

56:15.122 --> 56:16.372
Oh, man, that is sick!

56:16.373 --> 56:19.792
He absolutely bull-rushed that right
tackle. Bo didn't even have a chance.

56:19.793 --> 56:23.137
Yeah, I gotta give it to the kid.
He's got a wicked first step.

56:23.255 --> 56:25.723
- See what he does on the next play.
- All right.

56:29.928 --> 56:31.846
Speed kills. Look at that.

56:31.847 --> 56:33.639
Yeah, look at that.
He gets frantic.

56:33.640 --> 56:35.349
My favorite thing about rookie QBs.

56:35.350 --> 56:37.894
They get frantic when they
think they're gonna get hit.

56:37.895 --> 56:38.978
Although I gotta give him credit.

56:38.979 --> 56:40.521
Barrio' those two plays,
he was brilliant.

56:40.522 --> 56:43.400
He threw four TDs, including
the last one to win it.

56:45.819 --> 56:46.944
Take us down to that.

56:46.945 --> 56:48.446
Yeah.

56:52.117 --> 56:55.746
Looking downfield, staying calm.

56:56.163 --> 56:58.414
Sonny, this guy's textbook.

56:58.415 --> 57:01.959
Man, this kid is strong.
That's impressive.

57:01.960 --> 57:06.306
That's pure Roethlisberger.
He's pro-ready. End of story.

57:06.673 --> 57:08.174
Take it back.

57:08.634 --> 57:12.138
Rewind that back to the
start of the play.

57:12.471 --> 57:14.348
Just stop right here.

57:14.514 --> 57:15.681
What's missing?

57:15.682 --> 57:16.807
Fullback.

57:16.808 --> 57:18.309
But Wisconsin runs most of their

57:18.310 --> 57:20.019
passing plays out of
an empty backfield.

57:20.020 --> 57:22.363
No, not what I'm
lookin' at. Try again.

57:25.275 --> 57:27.152
Where's Vontae?

57:29.821 --> 57:32.281
You know what, Sonny?
I think he got ejected.

57:32.282 --> 57:34.200
- He got ejected from the game?
- Yeah.

57:34.201 --> 57:35.284
For what?

57:35.285 --> 57:37.119
Yeah, in the third
quarter, after he stripped

57:37.120 --> 57:39.038
the ball from Callahan
and scored that TD.

57:39.039 --> 57:40.539
He gave the ball to a fan.

57:40.540 --> 57:42.375
When he got flagged
for it, he went nuts,

57:42.376 --> 57:44.168
touched the refs. So
they threw him out.

57:44.169 --> 57:46.003
Bonehead move.

57:46.004 --> 57:47.676
Let's see that.

58:11.738 --> 58:14.490
This is college. What's
he thinkin', you know?

58:16.743 --> 58:18.745
See? That's it.

58:18.912 --> 58:20.037
There you go.

58:20.038 --> 58:22.498
He was showing off. You
can't do that in college.

58:22.499 --> 58:24.797
You can't hand the
ball to some girl.

58:26.545 --> 58:28.879
That's not some girl.

58:28.880 --> 58:31.428
That's not some girl, guys.
That's his sister.

58:34.636 --> 58:37.264
She died about six months later.

58:38.265 --> 58:41.268
Boo-friggin'-hoo.

58:41.393 --> 58:43.561
We ain't runnin' an
after-school special here.

58:43.562 --> 58:45.312
We're runnin' a football team,

58:45.313 --> 58:48.733
whose offense was ranked 28th
in the league last year.

58:48.734 --> 58:50.907
And I still need a runnin' back.

59:15.302 --> 59:16.469
What can I say, Rich?

59:16.470 --> 59:19.305
I love being here,
I love feeling the energy,

59:19.306 --> 59:21.807
and I love having the
number one pick.

59:21.808 --> 59:23.392
I hope that you would
love having it,

59:23.393 --> 59:25.478
because you sure gave
up a ton to get it.

59:25.479 --> 59:27.605
For the record,
I didn't do anything.

59:27.606 --> 59:29.482
And "ton" is a relative word.

59:29.483 --> 59:30.566
Playing coy. I like it.

59:30.567 --> 59:32.818
Come on, just between two
guys, forget the cameras,

59:32.819 --> 59:34.612
who're you gonna take,
number one overall?

59:34.613 --> 59:38.616
Well, I think it would be
unsportsmanlike, spoil the surprise.

59:38.617 --> 59:41.961
Anthony Molina. Not
giving me anything.

59:46.083 --> 59:47.249
What?

59:47.250 --> 59:48.334
Just please come with me.

59:48.335 --> 59:50.929
What? Oh, no, not back in there.

01:00:01.598 --> 01:00:03.145
So?

01:00:04.518 --> 01:00:06.816
So, what do you want?

01:00:09.856 --> 01:00:12.199
Honestly...

01:00:17.656 --> 01:00:20.033
I don't want to be a secret.

01:00:23.120 --> 01:00:24.712
Okay.

01:00:27.833 --> 01:00:29.416
Let's not be a secret.

01:00:33.380 --> 01:00:35.177
Excuse me.

01:00:36.633 --> 01:00:38.467
- Jesus, Rick!
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

01:00:38.468 --> 01:00:40.469
The head of security said he
wanted to talk to Mr. Weaver.

01:00:40.470 --> 01:00:42.472
He said it was urgent.

01:00:42.556 --> 01:00:44.723
- Ralph.
- Sonny.

01:00:44.724 --> 01:00:46.183
- Ali.
- Ralph.

01:00:46.184 --> 01:00:47.810
Everybody cozy?

01:00:48.895 --> 01:00:50.396
Good.

01:00:50.397 --> 01:00:54.572
Sonny, if you don't mind, I've got
something for you in my office.

01:01:00.448 --> 01:01:02.408
Got a new Callahan story for you.

01:01:02.409 --> 01:01:04.243
Not sure I want to hear it.

01:01:04.244 --> 01:01:06.912
You know, you hung me out to dry
pretty good with the last one.

01:01:06.913 --> 01:01:08.831
Just talked to Jack
Tate in Washington.

01:01:08.832 --> 01:01:11.250
He said when they found out
they had the number five pick,

01:01:11.251 --> 01:01:13.169
first thing they did was send
a copy of their playbook

01:01:13.170 --> 01:01:15.004
to all the guys they
were interested in.

01:01:15.005 --> 01:01:16.589
Right. We do the same thing.

01:01:16.590 --> 01:01:19.091
No, no, they put a little
special twist on it.

01:01:19.092 --> 01:01:21.594
They tape a $100 bill
to the last page.

01:01:21.595 --> 01:01:22.761
Why?

01:01:22.762 --> 01:01:24.430
So when they're
interviewin' the guys

01:01:24.431 --> 01:01:26.557
and they ask 'em if they'd
read the whole playbook,

01:01:26.558 --> 01:01:28.726
of course all of 'em
are gonna say yes.

01:01:28.727 --> 01:01:32.271
'Bout half of 'em, they mention the
money. But the other half don't.

01:01:32.272 --> 01:01:34.315
So, when they tell 'em
about the $100 bill,

01:01:34.316 --> 01:01:35.608
most of the guys get embarrassed.

01:01:35.609 --> 01:01:36.942
They get flustered.
They fess up that

01:01:36.943 --> 01:01:38.903
they didn't read the whole thing.

01:01:38.904 --> 01:01:41.447
But ask me what your
boy Bo Callahan did.

01:01:41.448 --> 01:01:43.449
You know, I really hate
playing this game with you.

01:01:43.450 --> 01:01:45.117
Ask.

01:01:45.118 --> 01:01:47.791
All right. What did Bo Callahan do?

01:01:48.914 --> 01:01:50.631
Neither.

01:01:50.874 --> 01:01:53.752
He said that he'd read it, and
then he didn't say anything.

01:01:55.462 --> 01:01:56.963
So?

01:01:57.047 --> 01:02:00.299
He didn't know about the
$100 bill, Sonny. He lied.

01:02:00.300 --> 01:02:01.842
He never read the whole playbook.

01:02:01.843 --> 01:02:03.135
So? A lot of guys don't.

01:02:03.136 --> 01:02:04.887
Yes. But when they
confront him about it

01:02:04.888 --> 01:02:07.473
and they tell him about
the money, he lied again.

01:02:07.474 --> 01:02:08.599
He said something like,

01:02:08.600 --> 01:02:11.819
"Oh, yeah. Now I remember.
Good one. Good one, guys."

01:02:11.978 --> 01:02:14.647
