you the Super Bowl."

01:02:41.341 --> 01:02:42.967
Nice.

01:02:42.968 --> 01:02:44.426
Don't you wanna know
who that kid was?

01:02:44.427 --> 01:02:46.304
No!

01:02:47.013 --> 01:02:49.436
It was Brian Drew.

01:02:53.019 --> 01:02:55.192
It was Brian Drew.

01:03:19.004 --> 01:03:20.504
Hey, Zotti.

01:03:20.505 --> 01:03:22.298
Texans thinkin' of makin' a move?

01:03:22.299 --> 01:03:24.717
Talk to me about Vontae Mack.

01:03:24.718 --> 01:03:26.218
<i>Why? What do you wanna know?</i>

01:03:26.219 --> 01:03:27.720
Who cares why?

01:03:28.722 --> 01:03:29.888
But you...

01:03:29.889 --> 01:03:31.890
You're thinkin' of
pickin' him at 15?

01:03:31.891 --> 01:03:34.018
He's got potential, no?

01:03:34.019 --> 01:03:36.738
Friend-to-friend, what
else do I need to know?

01:03:37.731 --> 01:03:40.232
Well, he's a great kid.

01:03:40.233 --> 01:03:41.317
Come on!

01:03:41.318 --> 01:03:43.068
That's what I know!

01:03:43.069 --> 01:03:44.820
Quit playing games.

01:03:44.821 --> 01:03:47.740
You didn't think he was gonna fall
in the second round, did you?

01:03:47.741 --> 01:03:49.033
Somebody's gonna pick him, Sonny.

01:03:49.034 --> 01:03:50.911
Tell me why that shouldn't be me.

01:03:51.411 --> 01:03:53.834
I'd never tell you
how to do your job.

01:03:54.080 --> 01:03:55.873
You find something with him?

01:03:55.874 --> 01:03:58.422
I didn't say that.

01:03:59.252 --> 01:04:01.299
You didn't not say that.

01:04:01.921 --> 01:04:04.014
Good luck tonight.

01:04:11.473 --> 01:04:13.020
Stop runnin'!

01:04:15.518 --> 01:04:16.935
Any news?

01:04:16.936 --> 01:04:19.897
We just got off the phone
with Houston. They're at 15.

01:04:19.898 --> 01:04:22.617
With the Cleveland thing,
that might be your best shot.

01:04:23.068 --> 01:04:24.526
Fifteen?

01:04:24.527 --> 01:04:27.446
And I'm not 100% sure about that.

01:04:27.447 --> 01:04:29.365
What does that mean, man?

01:04:29.366 --> 01:04:31.617
It means it could be a long night.

01:04:31.618 --> 01:04:34.962
But stay positive. You never
know with these things.

01:04:40.418 --> 01:04:42.044
What's all this?

01:04:43.129 --> 01:04:45.172
Both of you? Really?

01:04:46.424 --> 01:04:48.301
Did you have a fire? Or...

01:04:48.635 --> 01:04:52.389
I do not need this today.
I really don't.

01:04:52.430 --> 01:04:53.931
You look terrible.

01:04:53.932 --> 01:04:54.973
Thank you.

01:04:54.974 --> 01:04:56.475
You really do.

01:04:56.476 --> 01:04:58.319
Thank you, too.

01:04:58.937 --> 01:05:02.281
We had the reading
of your dad's will.

01:05:02.899 --> 01:05:07.905
Would you believe, he wants his
ashes scattered on his field.

01:05:07.946 --> 01:05:10.164
The practice field? Here?

01:05:10.323 --> 01:05:13.325
Weaver Field. Yes.

01:05:13.326 --> 01:05:16.286
And I'd like to do it
as soon as possible.

01:05:16.287 --> 01:05:18.122
You can't be serious.

01:05:18.123 --> 01:05:19.623
Why? I'm not gonna bother anyone.

01:05:19.624 --> 01:05:22.501
I just wanna do it exactly
as he asked for it.

01:05:22.502 --> 01:05:27.178
And he wants you to read
this while we're scattering.

01:05:27.507 --> 01:05:29.341
It's a Gaelic blessing.

01:05:29.342 --> 01:05:31.640
Now? You're saying you
want to do all this now?

01:05:31.845 --> 01:05:35.347
All we have to do is walk out
on the 50-yard line with you...

01:05:35.348 --> 01:05:36.765
- You read the...
- With me?

01:05:36.766 --> 01:05:38.183
It's what he wanted.

01:05:38.184 --> 01:05:40.185
How the hell would you
know what he wanted?

01:05:40.186 --> 01:05:41.353
Please don't shout.

01:05:41.354 --> 01:05:43.856
Because I was at the will
reading. Unlike you.

01:05:43.857 --> 01:05:45.524
Isn't there an art
exhibition in New York

01:05:45.525 --> 01:05:47.276
that you have to be
at or something?

01:05:47.277 --> 01:05:49.194
This isn't going to
be a long affair.

01:05:49.195 --> 01:05:51.613
We just go out there, read the
prayer, dump the ashes, and go home.

01:05:51.614 --> 01:05:52.698
No!

01:05:52.699 --> 01:05:54.325
Is everything okay?

01:05:56.369 --> 01:05:58.212
Everything's fine.

01:05:59.497 --> 01:06:01.965
Ali, this is my ex-wife, Angie.

01:06:03.460 --> 01:06:05.052
- Hello.
- Hi.

01:06:05.378 --> 01:06:06.545
Hi, Barb.

01:06:06.546 --> 01:06:08.172
How you doin', Amy?

01:06:09.382 --> 01:06:12.556
"Ali." You know it's Ali.

01:06:13.011 --> 01:06:15.058
She's the...

01:06:15.388 --> 01:06:17.389
Oh, her. Oh.

01:06:17.390 --> 01:06:18.724
Yeah. That's me.

01:06:18.725 --> 01:06:20.559
Get us some coffee,
will you, sweetie?

01:06:20.560 --> 01:06:22.227
Mom, that's not her job.

01:06:22.228 --> 01:06:24.146
- It's okay. I can get 'em coffee.
- I'll have a green tea.

01:06:24.147 --> 01:06:25.689
No, stay. Just, please, stay.

01:06:25.690 --> 01:06:26.899
I'd like to have a coffee, Sonny.

01:06:26.900 --> 01:06:29.067
No. No. No coffee, Mom.

01:06:29.068 --> 01:06:31.403
You want to spread these goddamn
ashes, you do it tomorrow!

01:06:31.404 --> 01:06:32.905
- No.
- I'm serious!

01:06:32.906 --> 01:06:34.578
No!

01:06:38.244 --> 01:06:41.580
Now then, are you going to read this
prayer as your father asked you to?

01:06:41.581 --> 01:06:43.879
No, I'm not!

01:06:46.377 --> 01:06:48.379
Not today.

01:06:49.339 --> 01:06:50.931
Fine.

01:06:52.383 --> 01:06:54.760
I will do it myself.

01:06:57.013 --> 01:06:58.765
Good luck.

01:07:02.435 --> 01:07:04.562
How about some fresh air?

01:07:10.944 --> 01:07:13.445
Whoever thought it meant
that much to him?

01:07:13.446 --> 01:07:17.701
Naming a simple practice
field in his honor.

01:07:18.409 --> 01:07:22.129
God, he took pride in
the weirdest things.

01:07:23.289 --> 01:07:25.962
He was your father, Sonny.

01:07:28.628 --> 01:07:31.972
What was it? Why did
you hate him so much?

01:07:33.091 --> 01:07:35.559
I didn't hate my father.

01:07:38.096 --> 01:07:41.974
You know what, everyone always gives
me grief for firing my father.

01:07:41.975 --> 01:07:45.775
Well, you did. I was here that day.

01:07:47.814 --> 01:07:49.657
It was my mother.

01:07:50.191 --> 01:07:51.650
What?

01:07:51.651 --> 01:07:53.318
It was my mother.

01:07:53.319 --> 01:07:55.487
Look, don't get me wrong.
I'm the one who fired him.

01:07:55.488 --> 01:07:59.242
But it was my mother
who asked me to do it.

01:08:04.163 --> 01:08:06.290
My dad's doctors told
him that the stress

01:08:06.291 --> 01:08:08.750
of coaching was gonna
kill him, so...

01:08:08.751 --> 01:08:11.169
Of course, he refused to retire.

01:08:11.170 --> 01:08:13.630
So, now I have a choice.

01:08:13.631 --> 01:08:16.759
The time he has left at
home with my mother,

01:08:17.093 --> 01:08:20.679
or another year on the sidelines,

01:08:20.680 --> 01:08:25.777
where maybe he drops dead
on national television.

01:08:28.354 --> 01:08:30.356
So what do you do?

01:08:30.857 --> 01:08:33.529
I gave it to my mom
and I fired him.

01:08:34.484 --> 01:08:37.363
How come you never
told me that before?

01:08:37.529 --> 01:08:40.032
You know, there's already so
many versions of what happened

01:08:40.033 --> 01:08:41.867
that it's not really somethin'
I love talking about.

01:08:41.868 --> 01:08:43.493
You never told him?

01:08:43.493 --> 01:08:46.203
You let him believe that his
only son would just fire him?

01:08:46.205 --> 01:08:47.538
That's how we do
things in my family.

01:08:47.540 --> 01:08:49.212
Sonny.

01:08:51.044 --> 01:08:55.219
And all I ever wanted to do
was just get him a ring.

01:09:01.054 --> 01:09:03.227
Oh, jeez...

01:09:03.640 --> 01:09:05.140
What is this?

01:09:08.227 --> 01:09:10.479
They wanna pay their respects.

01:09:25.411 --> 01:09:27.082
Rick, what are you doing?

01:09:30.500 --> 01:09:32.923
Someone broke my computer.

01:09:34.712 --> 01:09:38.761
Can you believe that? I mean, this
thing had my entire life on it, and...

01:09:39.091 --> 01:09:41.935
I don't know. Who would do that?

01:09:42.886 --> 01:09:44.604
It was me.

01:09:45.598 --> 01:09:47.520
I threw it against the wall.

01:09:47.934 --> 01:09:50.435
Yeah. I'm sorry.

01:09:51.104 --> 01:09:52.938
Why would you do that?

01:09:52.939 --> 01:09:55.942
Look, I lost my head, okay?

01:09:56.109 --> 01:09:57.401
I've been steppin'
on my dick all day.

01:09:57.402 --> 01:10:00.951
Look, we'll get you a new one,
all right? We'll get you a better one.

01:10:02.448 --> 01:10:05.622
One with all the
bells and whistles.

01:10:07.120 --> 01:10:10.920
Look. You've been a soldier today,
all right? You don't deserve this.

01:10:11.124 --> 01:10:12.625
Okay?

01:10:12.875 --> 01:10:14.627
- Yeah.
- Good.

01:10:34.731 --> 01:10:38.150
Ladies and gentlemen, please
welcome to the red carpet,

01:10:38.151 --> 01:10:43.655
from the University of Wisconsin,
2014 Heisman Trophy winner,

01:10:43.656 --> 01:10:45.657
quarterback Bo Callahan!

01:10:49.996 --> 01:10:52.622
from Florida State University,

01:10:52.623 --> 01:10:55.459
running back Ray Jennings.

01:10:56.753 --> 01:10:58.505
How're you doin'?

01:11:10.516 --> 01:11:13.643
Ray, remind me when they
picked you. Was it first? Second?

01:11:13.644 --> 01:11:14.853
Mmm.

01:11:14.854 --> 01:11:17.903
It still hurts. 26th.

01:11:18.024 --> 01:11:19.946
Well, that's good, too.

01:11:20.151 --> 01:11:22.528
That's my number one
guy right there.

01:11:23.362 --> 01:11:24.863
Ready?

01:11:33.873 --> 01:11:35.457
You got this.

01:11:40.880 --> 01:11:43.132
Sonny, my man!

01:11:43.800 --> 01:11:46.428
Oh, I am excited to
hear your voice.

01:11:46.719 --> 01:11:49.137
We were wonderin' when you were
gonna call us with that good news.

01:11:49.138 --> 01:11:50.639
<i>Wanna talk to Bo, Chris.</i>

01:11:50.640 --> 01:11:52.733
Here's the man you wanna speak to.

01:11:53.226 --> 01:11:55.148
It's the Browns.

01:11:58.898 --> 01:12:00.650
This is Bo.

01:12:01.567 --> 01:12:03.193
Hey, Bo. How you doin'?

01:12:03.194 --> 01:12:05.737
<i>Well, I'm good, Mr. Weaver. Excited
to be a part of the NFL, you know.</i>

01:12:05.738 --> 01:12:08.912
Good, that's great, Bo.
Thrilled to hear that.

01:12:09.367 --> 01:12:11.660
Listen, I'm gonna ask you something

01:12:11.661 --> 01:12:14.412
and I want you to be
absolutely honest with me.

01:12:14.413 --> 01:12:15.956
You think you can do that?

01:12:15.957 --> 01:12:17.754
Yes, sure. Anything, Mr. Weaver.

01:12:19.544 --> 01:12:23.048
Bo, did your teammates come
to your birthday party?

01:12:23.381 --> 01:12:24.928
What?

01:12:27.218 --> 01:12:29.845
For your 21st birthday party,

01:12:29.846 --> 01:12:35.773
I'm asking, did your teammates at
Wisconsin come to that party or not?

01:12:38.437 --> 01:12:39.938
Look, Mr. Weaver,
this isn't somethin'

01:12:39.939 --> 01:12:43.113
I'm really very proud
of, sir, but...

01:12:46.279 --> 01:12:48.697
I don't really remember a single
thing from that night, sir.

01:12:51.909 --> 01:12:53.956
You know what?

01:12:56.539 --> 01:12:59.212
I don't remember mine either.

01:13:00.042 --> 01:13:02.465
Thanks, Bo. Talk to you later.

01:13:05.798 --> 01:13:07.470
What'd he say?

01:13:09.802 --> 01:13:11.554
Nothin'.

01:13:46.339 --> 01:13:47.965
Hey.

01:13:51.344 --> 01:13:53.141
You okay?

01:13:56.641 --> 01:13:59.143
Do I take Callahan?

01:14:00.770 --> 01:14:03.318
What do you want me to say?

01:14:04.899 --> 01:14:06.525
He's a winner.

01:14:07.360 --> 01:14:09.328
He is.

01:14:09.987 --> 01:14:13.281
He is. I mean, that's the word, right?
He's won everywhere he's been.

01:14:13.282 --> 01:14:14.908
I get that.

01:14:15.993 --> 01:14:18.828
But they said the same
thing about Ryan Leaf

01:14:18.829 --> 01:14:21.206
when he was the number
two pick in '98.

01:14:21.207 --> 01:14:24.881
No one said that about Tom
Brady when he went 199th.

01:14:26.295 --> 01:14:29.048
There's no such thing
as a sure thing.

01:14:30.549 --> 01:14:36.601
At the end of the day, all that
matters is what you think.

01:14:51.237 --> 01:14:53.614
Vontae! Vontae!

01:14:57.368 --> 01:15:00.996
Here we go, Brownies,
here we go! Whoo, whoo!

01:15:00.997 --> 01:15:04.717
Here we go, Brownies,
here we go! Whoo, whoo!

01:15:24.937 --> 01:15:27.105
Oh, dude, that's, like,
your fifth piece of pizza.

01:15:27.106 --> 01:15:29.691
I eat when I'm nervous. Don't
make me feel bad about it.

01:15:29.692 --> 01:15:31.609
Yeah, I get like that, too.

01:15:31.610 --> 01:15:34.238
Hey, guys. It's gettin' late.

01:15:36.198 --> 01:15:40.493
<i>History in the making here
today at the NFL Draft.</i>

01:15:40.494 --> 01:15:42.996
<i>Already fascinating
twists and turns</i>

01:15:42.997 --> 01:15:45.540
<i>as the Seattle Seahawks
and the Cleveland Browns</i>

01:15:45.541 --> 01:15:50.763
<i>have engaged in a historic trade
just hours before this moment.</i>

01:16:00.222 --> 01:16:02.474
Here's the Commissioner.

01:16:14.320 --> 01:16:19.451
Welcome to primetime and
the 2014 NFL Draft.

01:16:19.575 --> 01:16:23.079
This is an exciting
night for our players,

01:16:23.245 --> 01:16:24.837
our teams,

01:16:24.997 --> 01:16:26.873
and for you, the fans.

01:16:30.419 --> 01:16:34.674
The season begins tonight,
so let's kick it off.

01:16:34.757 --> 01:16:39.763
The 2014 NFL Draft
is officially open.

01:16:43.432 --> 01:16:47.311
After an earlier trade with
the Seattle Seahawks today,

01:16:47.394 --> 01:16:50.272
the Cleveland Browns
are now on the clock.

01:16:52.900 --> 01:16:55.527
Where the hell is Sonny, guys?
We're on the clock here.

01:16:55.528 --> 01:16:57.862
- I don't know.
- Yeah. Should be here.

01:16:57.863 --> 01:16:59.614
<i>Okay. So the Browns
now have 10 minutes</i>

01:16:59.615 --> 01:17:01.407
<i>on the clock to make a choice.</i>

01:17:01.408 --> 01:17:03.576
<i>And if they don't do
that in that time,</i>

01:17:03.577 --> 01:17:06.121
the team picking behind
them can then jump up

01:17:06.122 --> 01:17:09.249
and potentially steal away the
player the Browns wanted.

01:17:09.250 --> 01:17:13.044
It's a situation we saw play out in
2003 with the Minnesota Vikings

01:17:13.045 --> 01:17:17.095
<i>and it happened again in 2011
with the Baltimore Ravens.</i>

01:17:25.641 --> 01:17:27.100
Sonny!

01:17:27.101 --> 01:17:30.855
Yeah, thank God! Yeah, I was
wondering what you were doing.

01:17:31.480 --> 01:17:33.731
Yeah. It's go time, boss.

01:17:33.732 --> 01:17:37.452
Yeah, yeah. What name do you
want the Commissioner to say?

01:17:39.822 --> 01:17:41.323
All right.

01:17:52.001 --> 01:17:53.626
Hey, guys, he's here.

01:17:53.627 --> 01:17:55.920
Sonny, thank God. Where you
been? We're on the clock!

01:17:55.921 --> 01:17:57.755
Sonny, when are we
sendin' in the ticket?

01:17:57.756 --> 01:17:59.257
Yeah.

01:17:59.425 --> 01:18:01.301
I already sent the ticket.

01:18:01.302 --> 01:18:02.760
You did what?

01:18:02.761 --> 01:18:04.596
You sent the ticket?

01:18:04.597 --> 01:18:05.930
It's tradition! We all send it!

01:18:05.931 --> 01:18:07.682
New tradition, guys, all right?

01:18:07.683 --> 01:18:11.778
When this team starts winning,
we'll go back to that.

01:18:19.737 --> 01:18:21.863
And the pick is finally in.

01:18:21.864 --> 01:18:23.031
It's currently being brandished

01:18:23.032 --> 01:18:25.200
by some walkie-talkied individual

01:18:25.201 --> 01:18:27.294
taking it up to the
Commissioner's podium.

01:18:27.536 --> 01:18:31.336
<i>A big, humongous pick for
the Cleveland Browns.</i>

01:18:32.374 --> 01:18:34.876
<i>Now, to find out whose
name is on that card,</i>

01:18:34.960 --> 01:18:38.796
<i>here's the Commissioner ready
to make history in Cleveland.</i>

01:18:47.640 --> 01:18:51.940
With the first pick of
the 2014 NFL Draft,

01:18:53.812 --> 01:18:56.314
the Cleveland Browns select.

01:18:57.733 --> 01:19:01.945
<i>Vontae Mack, linebacker,
Ohio State.</i>

01:19:12.915 --> 01:19:14.499
Yes! Yes!

01:19:20.256 --> 01:19:21.798
These things happen.

01:19:26.011 --> 01:19:28.513
That's what you decided to do?

01:19:34.561 --> 01:19:37.105
An absolute stunner here
at Radio City Music Hall.

01:19:37.106 --> 01:19:39.315
The Cleveland Browns, with
the number one overall pick,

01:19:39.316 --> 01:19:41.609
take Vontae Mack!

01:19:41.610 --> 01:19:43.695
<i>Unbelievable to me
that Sonny Weaver Jr.</i>

01:19:43.696 --> 01:19:45.822
<i>would make a deal of this magnitude</i>

01:19:45.823 --> 01:19:47.365
<i>and come away with this.</i>

01:19:47.366 --> 01:19:49.033
Forget about Vontae
Mack for a second.

01:19:49.034 --> 01:19:50.702
They could have had Bo Callahan.

01:19:50.703 --> 01:19:53.204
He's the surefire slam-dunk
number one pick.

01:19:53.205 --> 01:19:54.789
We all knew it comin' in here.

01:19:54.790 --> 01:19:57.709
If I'm Brian Drew, current
quarterback of the Cleveland Browns,

01:19:57.710 --> 01:19:59.085
I better play good.

01:20:30.534 --> 01:20:32.452
Yeah. No, no. I realize that.

01:20:32.453 --> 01:20:34.329
He wants to talk to him right now.

01:20:34.330 --> 01:20:35.580
Then call me back.

01:20:35.581 --> 01:20:36.622
I'm sorry, sir...

01:20:36.623 --> 01:20:38.041
Just get in the damn car.

01:20:38.042 --> 01:20:39.542
This is Anthony.

01:20:39.543 --> 01:20:41.377
Tell Sonny I'm on
my way to Teterboro

01:20:41.378 --> 01:20:45.974
and I will literally be in his face in
an hour and he will talk to me then.

01:20:46.091 --> 01:20:47.968
I will, sir.

01:20:48.385 --> 01:20:50.762
- Safe trip, sir.
- Thank you, Marvin.

01:21:04.276 --> 01:21:05.823
It's Sonny.

01:21:10.699 --> 01:21:12.784
Sonny Weaver Jr.

01:21:12.785 --> 01:21:16.164
Congratulations, Vontae.
You're a Cleveland Brown.

01:21:16.663 --> 01:21:19.541
I'm a Cleveland Brown!

01:21:19.833 --> 01:21:21.626
Car's gonna be picking
you up in 10 minutes,

01:21:21.627 --> 01:21:23.294
and we're flying you to Cleveland.

01:21:23.295 --> 01:21:25.012
You think you can manage that?

01:21:25.130 --> 01:21:28.474
Oh...

01:21:33.555 --> 01:21:36.103
You need to get back inside.

01:21:36.308 --> 01:21:38.267
What just happened?

01:21:38.268 --> 01:21:40.736
This is the NFL Draft.

01:21:40.771 --> 01:21:43.990
These things happen all the time.

01:21:44.108 --> 01:21:46.109
Now trust me.

01:21:46.110 --> 01:21:49.153
These teams, they don't want
a quarterback that panics.

01:21:49.154 --> 01:21:52.032
I need you to come inside, now.

01:21:57.746 --> 01:21:59.293
Come on.

01:22:09.716 --> 01:22:12.685
You picked Vontae. Wow.

01:22:14.096 --> 01:22:17.975
Three first-round picks to get the
guy I could have gotten all along.

01:22:19.393 --> 01:22:21.978
Jesus, I used to think
I was good at this.

01:22:21.979 --> 01:22:23.729
Well, that remains to be seen.

01:22:24.982 --> 01:22:28.611
Sometimes, the correct
path is the tortured one.

01:22:29.862 --> 01:22:31.946
It's a gift, Sonny.

01:22:31.947 --> 01:22:35.576
You see things other people
don't see. It's one of the things...

01:22:38.412 --> 01:22:41.415
It's one of the things
I love about you.

01:22:46.962 --> 01:22:48.463
Excuse me.

01:22:49.256 --> 01:22:50.923
You're not gonna believe
what's happening.

01:22:50.924 --> 01:22:52.425
<i>You know, I think back, Deion,</i>

01:22:52.426 --> 01:22:56.554
<i>and I go back to 1983 and I start
thinkin' about Dan Marino.</i>

01:22:56.555 --> 01:22:58.222
<i>He was the sixth
quarterback taken...</i>

01:22:58.223 --> 01:22:59.765
Holy shit!

01:22:59.766 --> 01:23:00.850
What's goin' on?

01:23:00.851 --> 01:23:02.773
He's dropping.

01:23:02.895 --> 01:23:03.978
What?

01:23:03.979 --> 01:23:06.189
Picks number two and three
are not Bo Callahan.

01:23:06.190 --> 01:23:07.987
Nobody's pickin' him.

01:23:10.068 --> 01:23:11.861
<i>Just last year.</i>

01:23:11.862 --> 01:23:13.404
<i>Geno Smith drops out
of the first round,</i>

01:23:13.405 --> 01:23:16.491
<i>and there are all kinds of
rumors goin' on right now,</i>

01:23:16.492 --> 01:23:19.165
<i>"Why is this kid dropping and..."</i>

01:23:19.453 --> 01:23:21.746
Everybody's freaking out, Sonny.

01:23:21.747 --> 01:23:24.841
St. Louis went with Anderson.
Miami took Palmer.

01:23:26.710 --> 01:23:27.877
Who's picking fourth?

01:23:27.878 --> 01:23:29.425
Arizona.

01:23:29.922 --> 01:23:31.464
Are they gonna take Callahan?

01:23:31.465 --> 01:23:33.841
They should, but everybody's
off their game.

01:23:33.842 --> 01:23:36.427
Rams and the Dolphins, both
went with their expected picks,

01:23:36.428 --> 01:23:38.179
even though Bo was still available.

01:23:38.180 --> 01:23:40.723
Everybody's panickin' 'cause
Callahan's still there.

01:23:40.724 --> 01:23:44.524
Jesus, what if he drops to seventh?
Seahawks have seventh.

01:23:44.686 --> 01:23:46.562
What if they ended
up with Callahan?

01:23:46.563 --> 01:23:49.232
Well, then Tom Michaels
is the GM of the decade.

01:23:49.233 --> 01:23:52.443
I'm goin' to the can, to throw up.

01:23:52.444 --> 01:23:56.197
Okay. Denver has five.
Jacksonville has six.

01:23:56.198 --> 01:23:57.782
Yeah, but Denver's not
gonna take Callahan.

01:23:57.783 --> 01:23:59.283
They got Herrod, he's an All-Pro.

01:23:59.284 --> 01:24:02.458
So if Arizona balks, then
Jacksonville's all over him.

01:24:02.746 --> 01:24:04.789
Unless they balk, too.

01:24:04.790 --> 01:24:08.251
And our friend Tom Michaels
grabs him at seven. Shit!

01:24:08.252 --> 01:24:11.221
They have that kid GM down in
Jacksonville. What is his name?

01:24:11.463 --> 01:24:13.297
Jeff Carson.

01:24:13.298 --> 01:24:14.465
Rookie.

01:24:14.466 --> 01:24:16.764
Right, Jeff Carson.

01:24:41.368 --> 01:24:42.535
<i>Hey, buddy.</i>

01:24:42.536 --> 01:24:44.954
Holy shit, man. What do you
know? What do you know?

01:24:44.955 --> 01:24:46.547
<i>About what?</i>

01:24:46.748 --> 01:24:49.500
About this! About this thing!
What's wrong with Callahan?

01:24:49.501 --> 01:24:51.669
Nothing. We like Vontae better.

01:24:51.670 --> 01:24:54.171
The Rams took my pick.
Everything's out of whack.

01:24:54.172 --> 01:24:56.720
<i>Well, you still have time.</i>

01:24:58.260 --> 01:24:59.969
Arizona is picking right now.

01:24:59.970 --> 01:25:01.847
You're right. Hold on.

01:25:02.055 --> 01:25:06.976
<i>With the fourth pick
of the 2014 NFL Draft,</i>

01:25:06.977 --> 01:25:09.395
<i>the Arizona Cardinals select</i>

01:25:09.396 --> 01:25:13.357
<i>Robert Starks, cornerback,
Georgia Tech.</i>

01:25:17.029 --> 01:25:19.497
Wow. Arizona went corner.

01:25:20.032 --> 01:25:21.699
Shit. Starks was my backup.

01:25:21.700 --> 01:25:24.577
That's a tough break, but,
hey, Callahan's still in play.

01:25:24.578 --> 01:25:26.245
Who's pickin' fifth?

01:25:26.246 --> 01:25:28.956
The Broncos, and they're
not taking Callahan.

01:25:28.957 --> 01:25:31.250
They got Matt Herrod.
They don't need Callahan.

01:25:31.251 --> 01:25:32.376
Yeah, I think you're right.

01:25:32.377 --> 01:25:34.378
I think they're gonna go with
that big kid outta Oregon.

01:25:34.379 --> 01:25:36.802
Dearborne. Left tackle.

01:25:37.424 --> 01:25:40.343
Well, congratulations, Jeff.

01:25:40.344 --> 01:25:42.386
Looks like you got
yourself Bo Callahan

01:25:42.387 --> 01:25:44.555
to quarterback the
Jacksonville Jaguars.

01:25:44.556 --> 01:25:46.729
You gotta be straight with me.

01:25:47.184 --> 01:25:48.643
About what?

01:25:48.644 --> 01:25:51.479
What's wrong with Callahan?
Why is everyone passin' on him?

01:25:51.480 --> 01:25:52.772
Why did you pass on him?

01:25:52.773 --> 01:25:54.523
I told you. We like Vontae better.

01:25:54.524 --> 01:25:58.778
Damn it, Sonny, I'm about to
be on the clock here. Please.

01:25:58.779 --> 01:26:00.321
What's wrong with Callahan?

01:26:00.322 --> 01:26:01.739
Can I be frank with you?

01:26:01.740 --> 01:26:03.241
Yes.

01:26:04.534 --> 01:26:05.868
I think he's a bust.

01:26:07.037 --> 01:26:08.412
What?

01:26:08.413 --> 01:26:09.705
How? Why?

01:26:09.706 --> 01:26:12.425
I don't know. Gut feeling.

01:26:13.168 --> 01:26:16.045
To be honest, Jeff, it's a
character thing for me.

01:26:16.046 --> 01:26:17.380
But, look, I have other needs.

01:26:17.381 --> 01:26:19.757
So, if you wanna make
a trade for six,

01:26:19.758 --> 01:26:21.926
I can make that happen right now.

01:26:21.927 --> 01:26:24.220
You want six? Who are you takin'?

01:26:26.139 --> 01:26:27.848
<i>I can't tell you that, Jeff.</i>

01:26:27.849 --> 01:26:29.934
The question is, do you
want to make a trade?

01:26:29.935 --> 01:26:32.770
Because if you're not
sold on Callahan,

01:26:32.771 --> 01:26:35.064
you can still come out of here
with a handful of draft picks,

01:26:35.065 --> 01:26:37.108
you look like a seasoned pro,

01:26:37.109 --> 01:26:40.027
<i>and everybody wonders what
you're up to next year.</i>

01:26:40.028 --> 01:26:42.029
I don't know. I don't know, Sonny.

01:26:42.030 --> 01:26:47.081
Look, Jeff, every year someone comes
out of this looking like a donkey.

01:26:47.369 --> 01:26:49.537
<i>- Can you hear me?</i>
- Yeah.

01:26:49.538 --> 01:26:51.122
Good. Because tomorrow
I got a feeling

01:26:51.123 --> 01:26:53.625
it could be you if you
don't make this deal.

01:26:56.545 --> 01:26:59.505
Look, everyone else has a reason

01:26:59.506 --> 01:27:02.350
to pass on Bo Callahan. You don't.

01:27:03.427 --> 01:27:05.144
Give me six.

01:27:06.972 --> 01:27:09.181
Give me six and I'll give you
our second-round pick this year

01:27:09.182 --> 01:27:11.267
and our second-rounder next year.

01:27:11.268 --> 01:27:12.940
Do what?

01:27:13.520 --> 01:27:17.022
Oh! That sounds awesome,
Sonny. What am I, a jerk?

01:27:17.023 --> 01:27:19.400
I'm just spit-balling here, Jeff.

01:27:19.401 --> 01:27:22.987
<i>Two number twos for the
sixth overall? I'm not an idiot.</i>

01:27:22.988 --> 01:27:25.239
I'd give you ones, but
I already dealt 'em.

01:27:25.240 --> 01:27:27.700
Well, you're gonna have
to do better than that.

01:27:27.701 --> 01:27:29.243
Jesus, the clock.

01:27:29.244 --> 01:27:30.745
I know. Denver hasn't picked yet,

01:27:30.746 --> 01:27:33.123
but they will any
second, all right?

01:27:33.165 --> 01:27:36.589
Shit, Sonny, I need more. Tell me.

01:27:36.960 --> 01:27:40.179
What is the very best
that you can do?

01:27:51.391 --> 01:27:53.063
Final offer.

01:27:53.310 --> 01:27:55.936
Take our number two pick this year,

01:27:55.937 --> 01:27:58.731
next year, and the
next year after that.

01:27:58.732 --> 01:28:01.326
That's three years
of number two picks.

01:28:08.867 --> 01:28:12.667
Four. I want your next
four number twos.

01:28:14.915 --> 01:28:16.707
Nah, Jeff, I'm not gonna do that.

01:28:16.708 --> 01:28:19.293
Stay with me on planet
Earth here, all right?

01:28:19.294 --> 01:28:22.013
You know what I just
offered you is fair.

01:28:23.799 --> 01:28:27.269
So, three years of second-rounders?

01:28:27.427 --> 01:28:30.179
That's right. For
your pick right now.

01:28:30.180 --> 01:28:31.847
And you and your guys can regroup,

01:28:31.848 --> 01:28:35.397
figure yourselves out and relax.

01:28:39.439 --> 01:28:42.033
This is a good deal, Jeff.

01:28:44.194 --> 01:28:47.243
This is a good deal for both of us.

01:28:54.120 --> 01:28:55.204
Deal.

01:28:59.751 --> 01:29:01.919
Good, Jeff. You did good.

01:29:01.920 --> 01:29:04.764
Call it in. Call it in.

01:29:06.383 --> 01:29:08.100
Hey, this is Marx.

01:29:10.804 --> 01:29:12.806
We got something, Ken.

01:29:13.723 --> 01:29:15.975
- Cleveland's in this.
- And Jacksonville.

01:29:15.976 --> 01:29:17.477
Okay, give it to me.

01:29:18.895 --> 01:29:20.938
Okay, somebody get me Tom
Michaels on the phone.

01:29:20.939 --> 01:29:22.986
Tell me you didn't
just do that, Sonny.

01:29:24.943 --> 01:29:26.443
Michaels. Tom Michaels.

01:29:26.444 --> 01:29:27.528
Are we on the clock?

01:29:27.529 --> 01:29:29.446
Tell me you didn't just do that.

01:29:29.447 --> 01:29:30.531
We just got the number six pick.

01:29:30.532 --> 01:29:33.158
And, no, we are not on the clock.
Denver's on the clock.

01:29:33.159 --> 01:29:35.452
Okay, so we got six!
Who are we picking at six?

01:29:35.453 --> 01:29:37.121
Rick, can you get Marvin
on the phone now?

01:29:37.122 --> 01:29:38.289
Let me get this straight.

01:29:38.290 --> 01:29:41.292
In the span of one day, you
have managed to burn through

01:29:41.293 --> 01:29:44.503
three years' worth of number one and
number two picks, is that correct?

01:29:44.504 --> 01:29:45.588
Yeah.

01:29:45.589 --> 01:29:47.506
- I quit, Sonny.
- Don't quit.

01:29:47.507 --> 01:29:49.258
I can't coach a team that
doesn't have a future, Sonny.

01:29:49.259 --> 01:29:50.384
That's the way it works.

01:29:50.385 --> 01:29:51.677
I got Tom Michaels on the line!

01:29:51.678 --> 01:29:53.178
Sonny, are we trading six?

01:29:53.179 --> 01:29:55.602
Will everyone please just shut up?

01:29:56.558 --> 01:29:57.641
People, please,

01:29:57.642 --> 01:30:01.897
can I have a moment of goddamn silence
while I do my job here, okay?

01:30:03.648 --> 01:30:05.858
Look. Don't quit, all right?

01:30:05.859 --> 01:30:09.236
Just let me do my job here.
Just let me do this. Don't quit now.

01:30:09.237 --> 01:30:12.741
If, by the end of the night, you
still wanna quit, then quit.

01:30:12.824 --> 01:30:15.034
Just see what I do from here.

01:30:15.035 --> 01:30:16.785
Your show, Sonny.

01:30:16.786 --> 01:30:18.378
Tom Michaels is holding.

01:30:20.081 --> 01:30:21.790
You son of a bitch!

01:30:21.791 --> 01:30:23.542
Anthony, I need five
minutes, all right?

01:30:23.543 --> 01:30:25.461
Five minutes, and
then you can fire me.

01:30:25.462 --> 01:30:26.962
Sonny, you are a dead man.

01:30:26.963 --> 01:30:29.465
Mr. Molina. Mr. Molina.
Look at me. Look at me.

01:30:29.466 --> 01:30:31.926
Just give him a minute.
He knows what he's doing.

01:30:31.927 --> 01:30:33.260
Tom, it's Sonny.

01:30:33.261 --> 01:30:36.347
Jesus, Mary and Whatnot. Do I
owe you a thank you, Weaver?

01:30:36.348 --> 01:30:38.265
Jacksonville's on the clock

01:30:38.266 --> 01:30:41.352
and I'm one more crazy
shit-show from insanity.

01:30:41.353 --> 01:30:45.147
Can you imagine, scoring three
first-round picks and Bo Callahan?

01:30:45.148 --> 01:30:48.817
Lord God, let that infant
John Carson screw this up.

01:30:48.818 --> 01:30:51.111
It's Jeff Carson, Tom, and
he doesn't have the pick.

01:30:51.112 --> 01:30:52.704
I do.

01:30:54.240 --> 01:30:55.407
What?

01:30:55.408 --> 01:30:59.703
I just made a trade with Jacksonville.
I'm on the clock. It's me.

01:30:59.704 --> 01:31:00.788
Bullshit!

01:31:00.789 --> 01:31:01.997
<i>The Jacksonville Jaguars</i>

01:31:01.998 --> 01:31:03.248
<i>have made a trade.</i>

01:31:03.249 --> 01:31:07.674
<i>The Cleveland Browns now have the
sixth pick and are on the clock.</i>

01:31:11.383 --> 01:31:12.758
Sonny, what'd you give 'em?

01:31:12.759 --> 01:31:14.343
No time for that. I'm on the clock.

01:31:14.344 --> 01:31:16.470
I'm gonna pick Bo, Tom.
Unless you want him more.

01:31:16.471 --> 01:31:18.430
And if so, let's make a deal.

01:31:18.431 --> 01:31:20.308
We still have Bo Callahan?

01:31:20.684 --> 01:31:22.777
What the hell's goin' on, Sonny?

01:31:23.269 --> 01:31:24.853
Everyone thinks there's
something wrong

01:31:24.854 --> 01:31:26.355
with the kid, but you
don't, all right?

01:31:26.356 --> 01:31:27.481
You've done your due diligence.

01:31:27.482 --> 01:31:29.483
You're about to pull off
the move of the century.

01:31:29.484 --> 01:31:32.453
But you need my pick to do it.
So make me an offer.

01:31:33.863 --> 01:31:36.740
You've gone rogue.
You've gone renegade.

01:31:36.741 --> 01:31:39.539
Yeah, that's right.
That's exactly right.

01:31:39.869 --> 01:31:41.829
I could have gotten
Vontae at seven,

01:31:41.830 --> 01:31:43.288
but instead I trade up with you

01:31:43.289 --> 01:31:44.707
just so I could get him at one.

01:31:44.708 --> 01:31:46.959
Jesus Christ. You were
right about me, Tom.

01:31:46.960 --> 01:31:49.878
I am a crazy man. So, come
on, take advantage of it.

01:31:49.879 --> 01:31:51.596
What are you waitin' for?

01:31:55.093 --> 01:31:59.018
Make me a deal, Tom, at six,
and you get your boy wonder.

01:32:01.016 --> 01:32:02.563
What do you want?

01:32:05.520 --> 01:32:07.771
I want my number ones
back. All of 'em.

01:32:09.566 --> 01:32:11.900
That's crazy. Why would
I give them back?

01:32:11.901 --> 01:32:14.778
Because, at the end of the
day, no one's the wiser, Tom.

01:32:14.779 --> 01:32:16.030
You haven't lost anything

01:32:16.031 --> 01:32:17.156
and you get the quarterback messiah

01:32:17.157 --> 01:32:20.706
you've always wanted
for $7 million less.

01:32:25.498 --> 01:32:29.251
Nah. No, I can't do it. I'd look
like an idiot, like I panicked.

01:32:29.252 --> 01:32:30.878
<i>You take him. You
obviously don't want to.</i>

01:32:30.879 --> 01:32:32.546
<i>I'll stick with my draft picks.</i>

01:32:32.547 --> 01:32:34.965
Yeah, but you want
him, Tom, don't you?

01:32:34.966 --> 01:32:37.426
Seahawks fans want a
hero and you denied 'em.

01:32:37.427 --> 01:32:39.178
- Not that bad.
<i>- Don't lie to me.</i>

01:32:39.179 --> 01:32:41.388
I checked all the Seahawk
fan blogs and chat rooms.

01:32:41.389 --> 01:32:43.599
They're all calling for your head.

01:32:43.600 --> 01:32:45.142
Ever since you traded
away Callahan,

01:32:45.143 --> 01:32:46.852
the barbarians are at the gate.

01:32:46.853 --> 01:32:48.562
I don't care about that.

01:32:48.563 --> 01:32:51.942
Yeah, you do. You
and I both know it.

01:32:52.692 --> 01:32:54.693
I have the golden ticket now, Tom,

01:32:54.694 --> 01:32:59.290
and if I give it to you, you get to
save Seahawk football in Seattle.

01:33:01.618 --> 01:33:02.785
Um...

01:33:02.786 --> 01:33:06.163
How 'bout I give you
number two picks?

01:33:06.164 --> 01:33:07.748
No. Uh-uh. Uh-uh.

01:33:07.749 --> 01:33:10.334
No, I want my picks
back. All of them.

01:33:10.335 --> 01:33:13.295
I want all three years of
this team's future back.

01:33:13.296 --> 01:33:14.338
That's not fair!

01:33:14.339 --> 01:33:15.798
Well, you wanna cry about it, Tom,

01:33:15.799 --> 01:33:17.007
or you wanna make a little magic

01:33:17.008 --> 01:33:19.351
before the clock runs
out on both of us?

01:33:20.178 --> 01:33:23.263
$7 million cheaper solves
our salary cap problem.

01:33:23.264 --> 01:33:25.099
We're still gonna give
the fans what they want.

01:33:25.100 --> 01:33:26.350
Okay. Screw it!

01:33:26.351 --> 01:33:28.227
No more offer. It's
off the table, Tom.

01:33:28.228 --> 01:33:30.187
- I'm takin' Callahan.
- Whoa, whoa. No, no.

01:33:30.188 --> 01:33:31.563
Wait, wait!

01:33:34.734 --> 01:33:36.401
All right. You have a deal.

01:33:36.402 --> 01:33:39.200
<i>I'll give you your picks!
We have a deal!</i>

01:33:40.490 --> 01:33:41.991
What else do we need?

01:33:43.535 --> 01:33:44.993
Offense?

01:33:44.994 --> 01:33:46.370
Special teams. Putney! Get Putney!

01:33:46.371 --> 01:33:47.955
Yes! David Putney! Putney!

01:33:47.956 --> 01:33:49.833
Yeah. Putney.

01:33:51.292 --> 01:33:54.011
Hello? Sonny?

01:33:56.589 --> 01:33:58.340
I'm sorry, that deal's
now off the table.

01:33:58.341 --> 01:33:59.633
What?

01:33:59.634 --> 01:34:03.434
We live in a different world than
we did just 30 seconds ago.

01:34:04.097 --> 01:34:05.389
Come on.

01:34:05.390 --> 01:34:06.891
What?

01:34:07.267 --> 01:34:09.189
What do you want now?

01:34:11.437 --> 01:34:13.814
I want my picks back

01:34:14.440 --> 01:34:16.400
and I want David Putney.

01:34:16.401 --> 01:34:17.985
<i>I need a punt returner.</i>

01:34:20.321 --> 01:34:22.156
<i>Where the hell did that come from?</i>

01:34:22.157 --> 01:34:24.158
It doesn't matter.
I want all my picks back.

01:34:24.159 --> 01:34:26.660
And I want David goddamn Putney
just because I feel like it.

01:34:26.661 --> 01:34:28.120
- You're outta your mind.
- Yeah, I am.

01:34:28.121 --> 01:34:30.498
Haven't I proved that already?

01:34:30.748 --> 01:34:34.001
You make this deal right now,
Tom, and you get Bo Callahan.

01:34:34.002 --> 01:34:35.503
Say it with me.

01:34:36.754 --> 01:34:39.382
"You get Bo."

01:34:42.343 --> 01:34:44.783
Come on, Tom, say it with me,
you pancake-eating motherfucker.

01:34:54.439 --> 01:34:57.774
All right. Shit. Deal.

01:34:57.775 --> 01:34:59.484
Great! You're welcome.

01:34:59.485 --> 01:35:01.487
Confirm the trade.

01:35:02.614 --> 01:35:06.038
God damn it, I love this job!

01:35:10.079 --> 01:35:12.832
Hold on. Looks like Cleveland's
making another trade.

01:35:12.916 --> 01:35:14.291
We got a trade.

01:35:14.292 --> 01:35:15.959
Okay, this means we're
picking next, all right?

01:35:15.960 --> 01:35:18.087
Back at seven, where we started.

01:35:18.463 --> 01:35:20.881
Tom's gonna take Bo.
So who do we got?

01:35:20.882 --> 01:35:22.474
Ray Jennings.

01:35:25.970 --> 01:35:27.888
We take Ray Jennings.

01:35:27.889 --> 01:35:30.182
That's right. Cleveland royalty.

01:35:30.183 --> 01:35:31.934
Haven't I been telling
everybody that

01:35:31.935 --> 01:35:34.153
that's what we need,
a running back?

01:35:34.520 --> 01:35:36.355
Still wanna quit, Coach?

01:35:36.356 --> 01:35:37.857
What?

01:35:38.233 --> 01:35:40.442
Does this sound like a
team that you wanna coach?

01:35:40.443 --> 01:35:42.236
Because the Browns
are ready to roll.

01:35:42.237 --> 01:35:44.489
We just need the right
man at the wheel.

01:35:45.782 --> 01:35:47.658
I can coach this team.

01:35:47.659 --> 01:35:49.451
I know you can.

01:35:49.452 --> 01:35:51.828
Why don't you give
Ray Jennings a call?

01:35:51.829 --> 01:35:53.914
Ask him if he wants to be a Brown.

01:35:53.915 --> 01:35:56.964
Then tell him to pack his bags
so he can join us at our party.

01:35:57.293 --> 01:35:59.761
My pleasure, boss.

01:36:05.260 --> 01:36:09.230
You got some set of balls,
Sonny. Congratulations.

01:36:12.225 --> 01:36:13.726
Thank you.

01:36:24.070 --> 01:36:27.030
<i>After a trade with the
Cleveland Browns,</i>

01:36:27.031 --> 01:36:32.037
<i>with the sixth pick of
the 2014 NFL Draft,</i>

01:36:32.120 --> 01:36:36.250
<i>the Seattle Seahawks
select Bo Callahan.</i>

01:36:36.291 --> 01:36:39.886
<i>Quarterback, University
of Wisconsin.</i>

01:37:10.783 --> 01:37:12.284
Hello?

01:37:16.748 --> 01:37:18.340
Hold on.

01:37:21.127 --> 01:37:22.544
Hello?

01:37:22.545 --> 01:37:25.172
Ray? Coach Penn of the
Cleveland Browns.

01:37:25.173 --> 01:37:26.590
Hi, Coach.

01:37:26.591 --> 01:37:30.766
<i>How would you like to play
for your Pop's old team?</i>

01:37:43.358 --> 01:37:44.775
I'm gonna be a Brown.

01:37:48.529 --> 01:37:49.905
You're gonna be a Brown!

01:37:49.906 --> 01:37:51.865
General Manager Sonny Weaver Jr.

01:37:51.866 --> 01:37:53.742
took one pick in the first round,

01:37:53.743 --> 01:37:55.285
the number seven pick.

01:37:55.286 --> 01:37:58.789
He sprinkled it with fairy
dust, wished upon a star,

01:37:58.790 --> 01:38:01.541
and somehow, he turned it
into not one, not two,

01:38:01.542 --> 01:38:04.461
but three potentially
impactful players

01:38:04.462 --> 01:38:06.630
for his team next year. One pick!

01:38:06.631 --> 01:38:10.476
He took a chance and went with
his gut and took his guys.

01:38:10.551 --> 01:38:12.260
<i>Make no mistake about it.</i>

01:38:12.261 --> 01:38:14.805
<i>The Cleveland Browns are
his team now for sure.</i>

01:38:14.806 --> 01:38:17.724
<i>This is the Draft Day Browns
fans were waiting for.</i>

01:38:17.725 --> 01:38:19.935
<i>Sonny Weaver Jr. pulled it off.</i>

01:38:19.936 --> 01:38:21.853
When you were like,
"I want all my picks back,

01:38:21.854 --> 01:38:24.606
"and I want David goddamn
Putney because I feel like it!"

01:38:24.607 --> 01:38:27.442
Like, how did you
come up with that?

01:38:27.443 --> 01:38:28.568
I was pissed.

01:38:28.569 --> 01:38:29.986
<i>Here, look at who
we have right now.</i>

01:38:29.987 --> 01:38:31.279
<i>Let me break it down.</i>

01:38:31.280 --> 01:38:36.660
<i>Vontae Mack, the guy who plays
with more passion and inspiration</i>

01:38:36.661 --> 01:38:40.165
<i>than anyone in college
football, he's a Brown.</i>

01:38:40.289 --> 01:38:44.376
<i>Ray Jennings, the running back the
Browns have needed for years.</i>

01:38:44.377 --> 01:38:46.711
<i>A return man to help
out on special teams,</i>

01:38:46.712 --> 01:38:49.381
<i>and, Rich, just like we wanted,</i>

01:38:49.382 --> 01:38:53.802
<i>Brian Drew, back at
quarterback, where he belongs.</i>

01:38:53.803 --> 01:38:55.595
<i>I don't even wanna hear
about Bo Callahan.</i>

01:38:55.596 --> 01:38:59.015
<i>If he thinks Callahan's a bust,
who am I to argue with that?</i>

01:38:59.016 --> 01:39:02.352
<i>He turned nothin' into
a big-time somethin'.</i>

01:39:02.353 --> 01:39:03.854
Smile for the cameras, Coach.

01:39:03.855 --> 01:39:06.606
<i>This is a day for
Cleveland to celebrate.</i>

01:39:06.607 --> 01:39:08.733
We had a great day!

01:39:08.734 --> 01:39:13.697
Super Bowl! Super Bowl! Super Bowl!

01:39:21.581 --> 01:39:24.708
That was gonna go
down a different way.

01:39:24.709 --> 01:39:26.210
Mom?

01:39:27.420 --> 01:39:29.172
There you are.

01:39:30.339 --> 01:39:31.673
You okay?

01:39:31.674 --> 01:39:33.884
Yeah. It was just so
noisy downstairs,

01:39:33.885 --> 01:39:36.433
I had to get a few
minutes of quiet.

01:39:36.804 --> 01:39:38.977
We're taking off.

01:39:39.140 --> 01:39:41.517
You sure you're gonna be okay?

01:39:44.979 --> 01:39:47.063
I think your dad would have been

01:39:47.064 --> 01:39:49.783
very happy to coach
a team like this.

01:39:57.158 --> 01:39:59.331
I think so, too.

01:39:59.452 --> 01:40:01.078
Thank you.

01:40:05.041 --> 01:40:08.168
Look, we gotta go.

01:40:08.169 --> 01:40:11.548
Of course. It was a long day.

01:40:13.633 --> 01:40:15.726
Bye, Ali.

01:40:17.261 --> 01:40:19.513
Good night, Barb.

01:40:22.934 --> 01:40:24.435
Hey, Mom.

01:40:29.690 --> 01:40:31.988
We're gonna have a baby.

01:40:39.909 --> 01:40:41.752
You're gonna be a grandma.

01:40:45.331 --> 01:40:47.378
Thank you.

01:40:56.676 --> 01:40:58.428
Wow!

01:40:58.511 --> 01:41:00.308
That was big.

01:41:02.723 --> 01:41:04.725
I'll get my stuff.

01:41:45.016 --> 01:41:46.099
Joe.

01:41:46.100 --> 01:41:48.602
Hey, Anthony, you did a hell
of a job with the Draft.

01:41:48.603 --> 01:41:50.186
- Congratulations.
- Thanks, Jim.

01:41:50.187 --> 01:41:51.354
Very impressive, Anthony.

01:41:51.355 --> 01:41:52.897
Thanks, Bernie.

01:41:52.898 --> 01:41:55.241
I can't take all the credit.

01:41:55.443 --> 01:41:56.818
But I will.

